wrong, I felt sad, because it's desagreable when a relationship  
is ending.
label: sad

text:
A meeting with the family and the friends I felt dear and loved,  
sharing the gladness of being together at a birthday.
label: happy

text: When I saw a horror film.
label: fear

text:
When my sister took something that belonged to me without my  
permission.
label: anger

text: When I felt alone and without love.
label: sad

text:
After making an effort to enter at University I found a course  
and a school of higher education which were compatible with my  
experience and potentiality.
label: happy

text:
I had an important amount of money with me and felt fear of being  
assaulted.
label: fear

text:
When I realized that the person I was courting hadn't been really  
by my side for a long time already. He had deceived me and I let  
him deceive me.
label: anger

text: When I noticed that I do many things to the pregiudice of myself.
label: sad

text:
I felt joy when I passed the worst phase in my life and  
discovered how many people considered me important to them.
label: happy

text:
I felt fear some months ago of losing the person whom I loved  
when she said to me that she didn't love me.
label: fear

text:
I felt much anger and perhaps I feel it till now, against my  
girlfriend's sister who incited her to betray me just when I  
needed her very much. She didn't think of anything, simply  
passed over everything.
label: anger

text: When my dog died.
label: sad

text:
I didn't like my former fob and felt joy when I received a  
telegram offering me a new one that I though better and for which  
I had been waiting.
label: happy

text:
I was in a train where a fight occurred. One person who was there  
opened his handbag and took out a gun, another who fought too  
looked among his things for a weapon to fight.
label: fear

text:
Without the employer's knowledge and even without any  
communication their bank accounts were changed and their personal  
accounts closed.
label: anger

text:
My brother wanted me to buy a flute with him but I didn't accept  
afterwards I regretted it because he became sad.
label: sad

text:
The day that my boyfriend appeared at home with a pair of rings  
for our wedding.
label: happy

text:
One day I was near home, kissing my boyfriend in a car when my  
mother appeared and asked me to go home, because she didn't know  
about the event.
label: fear

text:
A ex-boyfriend tried to prejudice me before my fiancT and his  
family saying things about me that let his family worried. We had  
to postpone our wedding and we were already using our wedding  
rings. To be honest I didn't feel just anger, I felt hate.
label: anger

text:
The day that the results of the college entrance examinations for  
the S. Paulo University were published and I didn't find my name  
on the list. Entering this University was my greatest wish, and   
the fact of not having succeded caused a great frustration, and  
not only sadness.
label: sad

text: When people remember us and shows interest about what we do.
label: happy

text: When I had to talk with an important person about a job.
label: fear

text:
When my brother went out with my new shirt that I adored, and  
returned it dirty with grease.
label: anger

text:
I felt sadness when I notice that I'm not important for a  
determinate person. We do many things for a friend, and we see  
soon after, that he doesn't do anything for us, nor thinks of us.
label: sad

text:
I felt glad to live again when I went to a meeting about the  
"Knowledge". There are 4 techniques of meditation that connect  
you with the essence of the human being.
label: happy

text:
I received a phone call from a high school friend whose younger  
sister studied with me at the University and gave me a lift every  
moning. She was going to get married to a guy whom I knew too and  
who had died when he fell from a building, I was afraid to lose  
somebody since I had already lost a brother in an accident.
label: fear

text:
My grandmother is a highly authoritative person, who lives alone,  
is independent, but doesn't know to live without commanding the  
others. I hate this!
label: anger

text:
I am always sad when my boyfriend goes away. He lives and studies  
in an other city. We have gone steady for 2 and 1/2 years and  
everything is going very well, but sometime this situation makes  
me feel bad and very lonely.
label: sad

text: When I bought my car.
label: happy

text:
I was alone at home, a man forced the front door which was  
locked, forced and tried to open a window.
label: fear

text: When I had a serious argument with a dear person.
label: anger

text:
One night a very dear person said: "I hate you". Of course it was  
an impulse and this person didn't feel that about me. The person  
expressed regret, and everything was settled, but I can't forget.
label: sad

text: The birth of my daughter.
label: happy

text:
I should have given a test lesson to get a job. I had no courage.  
I didn't make the test.
label: fear

text:
Discussion with my mother about the way to educate my children. I  
felt anger against my mother.
label: anger

text: When my grandmother died.
label: sad

text:
I found a human "treasure" that I desired and got immediately. I  
didn't think about anything. When I touched him I imploded but I  
am whole.
label: happy

text:
I was in the dark room, it's insecure and has holes covered with  
wooden sheets in the roof the establishment had already been  
assaulted and could be assaulted again.
label: fear

text:
And she said absurd things, false things that filled my ears and  
inflated my head which seemed to be caught in a carcass where the  
heart wanted to explode and where the arm wanted to knock down  
the world.
label: anger

text:
One day I heard from a friend that the boy I loved had gone out  
with her and not with me.
label: sad

text:
One of the greatest joiy was when I succeded in acquiring a  
motorcycle through my own efforts.
label: happy

text:
I'm afraid of driving on the special seat of a mororcycle, mainly  
with certain colleagues who by exces of self-confidence drive  
beyond limits or measure in the traffic and the main victim is  
always the person who sits behind the driver.
label: fear

text:
I felt much anger when my fahter interferred in my relations with  
another person whom I liked very much, ending something that I  
adored.
label: anger

text:
One of the greatest sadness was when my grandfather died, because  
I loved him very much.
label: sad

text:
When I got a stereo walkman from my father when he had finacial  
difficulties. I thought that although he promised to give me that  
present, he was not obliged to do so.
label: happy

text: That someone would discover whom I really love.
label: fear

text:
When a colleague was rude with me because she didn't understand  
the subject about which I was discussing.
label: anger

text:
For not having succeded in getting the job as a translator that I  
wanted.
label: sad

text:
When I passed the whole weekend with my boyfriend, coming back  
home on Sunday afternoon he met my parents for the first time.
label: happy

text:
When there was a fight at home and my father threatened to throw  
a chair on my brother.
label: fear

text:
I felt anger against a person who told bad things about me in my  
absence.
label: anger

text:
After a disagreement between my parents, when I was alone with my  
father and my sister, the aggression continued, when my father  
tried to put me and my sister against my mother revealing facts  
that had happened in the past like a talk between my father and  
his mother in law where she told him that my mother was not quite  
save.
label: sad

text:
I was in the living room at home with an ex-boyfriend, it was  
nearly a year that we had separated, during the talk he began to  
remember our courting and gave me a long kiss.
label: happy

text:
I was with a friend in a stationed car when, suddenly a man  
appeared on my side and an other with a gun on his side the  
hold-up lasted a few minutes but it was terrible. I had never  
seen a gun so close.
label: fear

text:
I was on a farm with a few friends and during the talk I  
discovered that a friend of mine, was being betrayed by her  
boyfriend and a 3rd friend of ours.
label: anger

text:
I was watching television. It was about midnight when a very dear  
friend called saying that his father had died in an accident.
label: sad

text: Always when I meet the person I love.
label: happy

text:
When I and the person mentioned above had a suspicion of  
pregnancy.
label: fear

text:
When I left after the examination to enter the University, and  
even though I had studied the whole year I made a bad exam.
label: anger

text:
When I thought for an instant that a very good relationship with  
a person had finished.
label: sad

text: When I entered in the University after a year of struggles.
label: happy

text:
Practicing wind-surf my body was caught under the sail. On trying  
to get out my leg was caught in the lashing. I was afraid of  
dying by asphixia.
label: fear

text:
In the University we were convoked to a stroll like a freshman I  
was still innocent about the manipulation. On seeing the goal of  
the exaltation to poor character people, I felt anger on feeling  
myself mass of maneuver.
label: anger

text:
In a social situation I became interested in a woman. We talked,  
we laughed, we enjoyed each other. She desappeared for a few  
minutes, and a little after appeared with an other man.
label: sad

text:
A friend of mine travelled very far. I miss her but feel joy too  
because fer life is taking the right direction as she wants. So I  
feel joy for her mainly.
label: happy

text:
Motorcyclistic accident where for some minutes I didn't know if I  
was alive or dead, I remained "cold levered" during the situation  
but felt great fear.
label: fear

text: When I met my mother after months of absence.
label: happy

text: When I whatched a horror film on a Friday 13th.
label: fear

text:
Discussing with a certain person about a job I was getting and  
that perosn was negative and pessimistic.
label: anger

text: When I felt lack of aid from close friends.
label: sad

text: I got a present from a great friend (a dog).
label: happy

text:
There was a scene of shooting in front of my house, I was very  
afraid. Two armed men confronting. I didn't discover the reason  
of the incident.
label: fear

text:
I was waiting to receive the participation on the profits and did  
not receive it.
label: anger

text: I didn't get the job I wanted.
label: sad

text: When I can see my parents because now I am far from them.
label: happy

text: When I sit for examinations.
label: fear

text: Once, during a performance I did not sing the way I had to.
label: anger

text: When I got separated from the woman I loved.
label: sad

text: When I was admitted to the Bulgarian State Conservatoire.
label: happy

text: I am afraid if I'll finish the term.
label: fear

text: I was angry when my abilities of a singer were underestimated.
label: anger

text:
I feel sadness from the fact that I was not born with a better  
appearance.
label: sad

text: I have a new born child.
label: happy

text: I could have been killed by a falling object.
label: fear

text:
At a certain situation I felt myself neglected and undeservedly  
harmed.
label: anger

text: The sudden death of one of my parents.
label: sad

text:
Getting separated from my family for a week caused me a sense of  
sadness.
label: sad

text:
I felt joy most strongly some years ago, when I took part in a  
NH Competition and I was the first.
label: happy

text:
I feel fear when I only imagine I could lose confidence in my own  
abilities and powers. A similar feeling I feel sometimes before  
an exam.
label: fear

text:
I feel anger when I see a "parent" beating and punishing his child  
in the street. Recently I was a withness of a similar case.
label: anger

text:
I feel sadness when I only imagine that I could lose a close  
person. Some time ago I lost a man whom aI greatly respected.
label: sad

text: When my nephew was born. The birth was hard, it was a big baby.
label: happy

text:
Late one night I was pursued by gipsies who had no good  
intentions.
label: fear

text:
My brother accused me undeservedly before my parents. I was not  
guilty. He was misled by his wife.
label: anger

text:
When I left my boyfriend. I found another girl at his home but he  
did nothing to relieve the situation.
label: sad

text:
Some time ago I was present at the wedding party of two close  
friends of mine.
label: happy

text:
I was crossing the street together with some colleagues of mine  
when I suddenly found myself almost under the wheels of a truck.
label: fear

text:
Someone stole my ski at Vitosha and of course I was the one to be  
blamed. I left them without supervision.
label: anger

text: I got separated form my closest friend. He went to work abroad.
label: sad

text:
An encounter with a man whom I love, after a very long  
separation.
label: happy

text:
I woke up in the middle of the night of a nightmare, I was alone,  
it was very quiet and very dark.
label: fear

text:
A shop-assistant behaved rather roughly with me though she hadn't  
the slightest grounds for it.
label: anger

text:
I saw a friend of mine who had suffered a very heavy contusion  
after an accident.
label: sad

text: At a success of mine, at a real achievement.
label: happy

text: For the first time in my life telling someone I loved them.
label: happy

text:
When I was ringing up a guy who was my teen idol, and was in  
Auckland. I was really scared, I didn't know what to say or do.
label: fear

text:
When my mother decided to clean out my room and throw out what  
she thought was junk, without my knowing about it, so I returned  
home to find half my stuff gone.
label: anger

text: When I couldn't find my dog which was missing.
label: sad

text:
When I met my boyfriend and we discovered that we shared the same  
ideals and goals in life, and that we could share all our  
feelings and thoughts and felt that the world's not so bad when  
you have someone really close to share your life with.
label: happy

text: When I passed the driving test after three failures.
label: happy

text: When I nearly caused a traffic accident with my car.
label: fear

text:
When playing a football match, there was one player who made mean  
tackels, kicked at everything and did things having nothing to do  
with football.
label: anger

text:
A close friend decided to stop with his study and to go back  
home.
label: sad

text: For instance when a girl is interested in me and likes me.
label: happy

text:
Walking at friday night through Nijmegen, going to a pub or a  
disco.
label: fear

text:
I sensed this feeling when I passed successfully the second tour  
of a competition.
label: happy

text: I felt fear when my mother was heavily ill.
label: fear

text:
I felt anger against a colleague of mine during a rehearsal in  
acting. He hadn't learnt the text of an opera act in the course of  
several months and thus making difficulties for the rest of my  
colleagues.
label: anger

text:
I felt sadness when I had to get separated from the woman I loved  
who had to leave for her motherland.
label: sad

text:
I was happy when at difficult times I could find support in my  
friend and my fiancT, I was happy because of their spiritual and  
moral help which gave me new power to struggle. I was happy then,  
I felt it in my soul.
label: happy

text: I felt it at the same time when I felt disgust.
label: fear

text:
I felt it on the same occasion when I felt sadness which finally  
grew into anger.
label: anger

text:
My living and working conditions at home were unbearable. We used  
to live in a three room flat together with two more families. The  
discords caused a change - one of the families moved out. The  
other family stayed with us but I drifted away from my fiancT. In  
fact we were two families in the flat. Then I found myself alone  
in the struggle for this life because my fiancT did not stay next  
to me my grief and sorrow took on large proportions. I wanted to  
commit suicide but instead I threw myself against the cause of  
the irritation.
label: sad

text:
That was what I felt when I was finally accepted in the Bulgarian  
Conservatorie after I had applied a couple of years.
label: happy

text:
I experienced this feeling when the doctors found a nodule in one  
of my mother's breasts. It turned out to be an occlusion  
resulting from continious sucking but for a few days I was not in my  
reason.
label: fear

text:
I had an accident with a trafic police car that was packed at a  
curve without any visibility and against all traffic regulations  
in a strong snowstorm. As a result I still cannot repair my car  
because of the missing spare parts.
label: anger

text:
A sudden doubt made me run for a long time in a rainy autumn  
night. When I reached the intended place I saw my beloved in  
another man's arms. A sudden blow, grief, I cannot qualify it, it  
is painful for me to remember about it.
label: sad

text: My boyfriend made me a proposal.
label: happy

text:
I was to be given an audition to get a role. I had a competitress  
and I wasn't well prepared because I was ill.
label: fear

text:
A whole crowd of us went to a folklore festival. The instructor  
of the cast where my boyfriend played was traveling with us. We  
decided to catch the train that leaved early in the morning  
because we had business on the following day. The instructor  
tried to get the upper hand and made us catch the train in spite  
of everything, all the time he made me angry.
label: anger

text: When I quarrelled with my boyfriend.
label: sad

text:
When I heard what mark I had got at the entrance examination and  
I realized my admittance to the University was almost certain.
label: happy

text:
Once I was alone at home. I suddenly felt unwell and there was no  
one to help me and call First Aid.
label: fear

text:
When I was admitted to a Language school. On the day when I was  
informed by a message and my parents congratulated me.
label: happy

text:
When diving deep into the sea to reach the floor I felt  
breathless. I was cautious but I doubted I should be able to come  
to the surface and inhale.
label: fear

text:
When my friend (girl) promised to help me go to the hospital and be  
examined by good experts and she deceived me.
label: anger

text:
When I had stayed abroad for a long time and I had remembered  
about my friends and relatives. I felt sad and I wanted to see  
them as soon as possible.
label: sad

text:
When you are satisfied with something, when you achieve something  
you have striven to.
label: happy

text:
One fears many things, for example one fears going to the  
dentist. but as far as I am concerned this feeling is connected  
with the examination session.
label: fear

text:
When you are unjustly assessed at something you are sure to have  
been right.
label: anger

text:
For the loss of a close friend or relative, but you feel grief  
when you are away from home, too.
label: sad

text: They wanted something to happen but I didn't.
label: anger

text: I couldn't be with a girl on whom I was very keen.
label: sad

text: Having passed an exam.
label: happy

text: Having a car accident.
label: fear

text:
I shared a secret with a friend and it later turned out that he  
had revealed it to another person with whom I didn't get along very well.
label: anger

text: The loss of a very good friend.
label: sad

text:
I'm glad when I have good relations with my colleagues and most  
of all when we are at a party.
label: happy

text:
I experienced it once when we were on a drive. Our car passed by  
the one comming from the opposite direction at an incredibly  
small distance.
label: fear

text:
I get angry with people who attain certain status without  
deserving it, only with the support, authority and influence of  
other people.
label: anger

text:
I feel sad when I see things done against men and nothing could  
stop it - at least I think so.
label: sad

text:
I experienced it when I was accepted at the Medical Higher  
Institute.
label: happy

text: I felt it when I sat for my exam in anatomy.
label: fear

text:
I experience that feeling when I am unsulted without deserving  
it or when someone deceives me.
label: anger

text: When my grandfather died.
label: sad

text: After each successfully passed exam I am happy.
label: happy

text:
A friend of mine gave birth to a child. Very dangerous delivery.  
I was afraid for her and for the baby.
label: fear

text:
I get angry when someone imputes on me things I never can do,  
naturally negative. Servility, "connections", impudence, traits  
that get me mad.
label: anger

text:
My brother is a soldier. He promised to come home in a furlough  
but in the last moment he phoned and said that he could not come.
label: sad

text:
After the term exams I happened to meet a person that I respect  
and of whom I think very highly. It was nice that although we see  
each other rarely he had not forgotten me.
label: happy

text:
Few years ago my father was very ill. He stayed at a hospital for  
a long time. Then I experienced that terrible feeling that I  
might lose him.
label: fear

text:
I have a friend that I deeply trusted but it happened that I lost  
my confidence in her for which she herself was to blame.
label: anger

text:
We are several friends but our characters are very different and  
we inevitably split in the two extremes. It is sad that I myself  
don't know what to do, I try not to hurt either of the "parties"  
because there are conflicts to which one I should belong.
label: sad

text:
I experienced this feeling when I was accepted as a student.  
Because everything turned out different from my expectations.  
Although I passed the exam successfully I was accepted as a  
student only when I didn't expect it at all, namely at the  
beginning of September.
label: happy

text:
In the real sense of the word I experienced fear in my first  
months in the army. During my first night of duty. The cause for  
all this was a bear. I became panic sticken (may be for the first  
time) and even forgot that I had a gun.
label: fear

text:
When I was a soldier I quarrelled with my commander and may be in  
revenge for this he detailed me on duty two successive nights.  
Naturally he checked me up on the second night and found me  
asleep for which he sent me to the cells.
label: anger

text:
Sometimes I experience sadness for the Sports High School and for  
my unrealized dreams in the sport. Anyway there I spent six years  
of my life.
label: sad

text: Spontaneous picnic with sister and friend and children - great.
label: happy

text: Can think of no time that I have felt fear.
label: fear

text:
Teenage neighbours smashed my letterbox for the fifth time in a  
couple of months. It was a deliberate action of kids who had  
stayed in my home, had meals there yet took a dislike to my  
daughter.
label: anger

text: Guy I cared for went back to Canada to live.
label: sad

text:
Meeting with two of my friends I had not seen for 15 years. They  
were special people to me.
label: happy

text:
I was in the Korean War. We were attacked with mortars, me and  
companion. We stopped the jeep and ran for cover. Fortunately  
neither of us was hit but we both came close to being killed.
label: fear

text:
I've a situation of responsibility an employee who had a habit of  
being late, came late again after promising to say he would be at  
work in a few minutes, then arrived 3 hours later. He had been  
drinking.
label: anger

text:
My brother in law was dying of cancer. To see him wasting away  
was very sad.
label: sad

text:
When we took out an 84 year old woman for the evening and had  
hamburgers. She described the evening out as her happiest night  
out in 20 years.
label: happy

text:
While tramping on a narrow path two of us were confronted by a  
woman with two snarling dogs, demanding we get off the property -  
via a flooded river !
label: fear

text:
A friend got angry and drove "like a lunatic" with me and others  
in his car. I was angry about his dangerous driving.
label: anger

text:
A boy I look after for the probation service deliberately  
offended to provoke a reaction from the police.
label: sad

text:
I was seriously injured in a road accident. The very first steps  
I took with only one crutch to support me I felt so good. I enjoy  
being alive.
label: happy

text:
I was attacked, standing in a doorway, by a pack of 5 dogs,  
alsatians and farm dogs with my escape route blocked by a shut  
fence.
label: fear

text:
In the house where I live there is a new flatmate. His friends  
unfortunately are the dirt of society, intelligent, fashonable,  
rich and bored. At a party recently they were doing things I  
didn't like done in my house. I felt angry at them.
label: anger

text:
I was driving near my girlfriend's house and I decided to keep  
going because it was late and I would be back in the next few  
days anyway. The next day she was killed in a road accident.
label: sad

text:
When I found out that a set task (i.e. 2 essays and a test), the  
thought of which had oppressed me, were not on the date I had  
thought.
label: happy

text: When confronted and in my opinion hassled by the police.
label: fear

text:
When, for example, I was in my eleventh school year and I learned  
I had been classed for the Bulgarian Language and Literature  
National Olympiad.
label: happy

text:
When, for example, my grandfather fell seriously ill. It was  
necessary for him to be operated and I felt great fear of losing  
him because he is so dear to me.
label: fear

text:
When, for example, I was not approved to continue my studies at  
the Moscow University, no matter that I had the highest marks and  
in general the best records of all the candidates.
label: anger

text:
When, for example, I left for the first time my parents and I  
went to live in Sofia.
label: sad

text:
Some time ago a close relative of mine got off cheap with the  
worst.
label: happy

text: The last time I felt it was when I was coming home late at night.
label: fear

text: I haven't often felt this feeling. Once someone stole my garment.
label: anger

text: Recently I happened to remain alone for a long time.
label: sad

text:
Realizing one's desire, an experienced feeling of satisfaction  
from the realization of one's desires and aims.
label: happy

text:
Fear of the loss of a close friend, of feeling the ground slipping  
from under my feet.
label: fear

text:
Attitude to some manners of dealing and some "sanctioned"  
relations.
label: anger

text:
Feeling unable to preserve one's ideas and ambitions as innocent  
as they are when you are young.
label: sad

text: I won a sport contest.
label: happy

text: If a close relative's life is in danger.
label: fear

text: A close person lied to me.
label: anger

text: Getting separated from my girlfriend.
label: sad

text: When my son was born.
label: happy

text: Before an examination.
label: fear

text: Unjust punishment of a friend of mine.
label: anger

text: After the loss of a close relative.
label: sad

text: Meeting a loved man.
label: happy

text:
I felt a physical fear, if I can call it this way, today, in the bus where  
I was sitting on the first seat. While turning the driver didn't  
see the tram which was making a dash towards us (coming from the  
side I was), and whose driver intended to cross in yellow  
light.
label: fear

text:
At an unjust, or to be more precise, at a bureaucratic treatment  
of one's personality.
label: anger

text: When one is alone and knows that all the others are celebrating.
label: sad

text:
I sensed such a feeling when I understood I was admitted to the  
University. I was at home, the atmosphere was still, though I  
myself was full of suspense. I tried to do different things. When  
the telephone rang and...! Yes, of course there were other  
situations when I felt a similar feeling but I was unmindful of  
them.
label: happy

text:
This feeling I sensed quite recently. It was arisen by the  
terrific thought that I might lose the man I loved !
label: fear

text:
Anger I felt when my boyfriend told me he didn't mind breaking it  
off with me, i.e. each of us to take his own road. Because until  
that moment, he deliberately restricted our dates. The motives  
were brought to my knowledge later.
label: anger

text:
Sometimes, when I'm alone I am seized by this feeling. But it  
always helps me to come round and at the same time to judge if it  
is worth. Very often this feeling is caused to me by people -  
friends who I love and respect.
label: sad

text: When I was admitted to the University.
label: happy

text:
I had to have my tonsils out. I had been making up my mind almost  
for a year - I was afraid. But during the two hours in the  
hospital room, while I was waiting to be called for the operation I  
felt a real fear - of the pain, of what they were going to do to  
me, of the unknown.
label: fear

text:
In a conversation my boyfriend expressed definite and quite  
pretentious opinions and he took up an attitude towards a theory  
which he himself had never known. His information was from  
fortuitous sources.
label: anger

text:
Summer, heavy rain, storm - I was standing with my face stick to  
the window: the childhood, something was going away forever this  
summer, I was leaving my home, I was going to study in another  
town, for the first time I was leaving my parents, friends, I had  
to manage myself, a long and loved period of my life was over - I  
was crying.
label: sad

text: When I understood that I was admitted to the University.
label: happy

text:
I felt this feeling when one day my landlord's cat had crept  
under my bed and I couldn't cope with it during an hour and a  
half.
label: fear

text:
I feel this feeling when I am to fill in a questionnaire or a  
form.
label: anger

text: When the man I loved decided to leave me forever.
label: sad

text:
A quarrel was followed by the decision of leaving a person close  
to me. Several days later my regret was great. I was beside  
myself. Quite unexpectedly he came and the conflict was calmly  
solved. I was glad at the possibility to be with him.
label: happy

text:
One evening I was watching the news on TV. Again they were  
talking about the danger of war. Suddenly I imagined what it  
might mean for me, for my friends, for the people close to me. I  
felt it a very near and possible event.
label: fear

text:
Unfair and unjust attitude toward a person close to me, what I  
was the witness of, caused anger in me.
label: anger

text:
The thought that I'll never sit at the school desk again, caused  
a deep grief at the end of my eleventh form.
label: sad

text: When I understood I was admitted to the Sofia University.
label: happy

text:
I broke my knee when I was skiing over "Yastrebetz" (a racing  
track in a Bulgarian winter resort).
label: fear

text:
The doctors from Belogradchik town determined a wrong diagnosis  
to my son. A month later, after some complex examinations at ISUL  
(A medical institute in Sofia), the diagnosis was categorically rejected.
label: anger

text:
My son lives with my parents in the country and I feel this  
feeling always when leaving for Sofia, but the last time it was  
quite strong.
label: sad

text:
I am a sportwoman as well. I felt joy when after an year of  
practice, at a contest, I covered the norms for "a master of sports".
label: happy

text:
I felt fear once, when the car in which I travelled directed  
towards the precipice along the road.
label: fear

text:
When I see how people around me pass by certain unjustice because  
of indifference or cowardice.
label: anger

text: When I left a man in whom I really believed.
label: sad

text: When I was admitted to the University.
label: happy

text: When I broke my leg I felt fear.
label: fear

text: When someone lies to me.
label: anger

text: At an unjust insult or injure.
label: sad

text: When my affairs with the girl I love settled positively.
label: happy

text:
In a dam lake, when the water was let flow to water the plants  
and I and two other boys were near the water pit. We rescued  
ourselves only thanks to the flippers and the tyre that was with  
us.
label: fear

text:
It was quite recently, at the football match between the national  
teams of Bulgaria and France. I felt strong anger with the Scottish  
referee who ran the match quite partially.
label: anger

text:
When I am alone and listen to a song which I like very much and  
which I had listened before together with friends.
label: sad

text:
I passed successfully the preliminary exam for a participation in  
the children Assembly.
label: happy

text:
I was alone in my room at the boarding house when at 12 o'clock  
someone knocked violently on the door.
label: fear

text:
A friend of mine promised to come with me to the cinema but he  
didn't come.
label: anger

text:
I felt sadness when I remembered my former boyfriend with whom I  
got separated an year ago and when comparing him with my present  
one with whom things are not much of a success.
label: sad

text: Bulgaria won a football match against France.
label: happy

text: I was going to knock down a pedestrian with my car.
label: fear

text: I was neglected undeservedly.
label: anger

text: My grandmother died.
label: sad

text: I felt joy when my two twin sisters were born.
label: happy

text:
The night before my wife had given birth to our twins. I felt  
fear in the hospital yard, I feared if everything was going to be  
in order.
label: fear

text:
About a month ago the Regional Council refused to pay my wife the  
due maternity benefit, because of bureaucratic reasons.
label: anger

text:
Some months ago my wife gave birth to twin sisters. She had no  
idea of looking after babies and she felt quite oppressed. The  
fact that I couldn't help her caused grief to me.
label: sad

text:
The period when I was pregnant and when I gave birth to my son.  
I can say those were the happiest months in my life.
label: happy

text:
A fear from the loss of a close friend as a result of his  
behavior.
label: fear

text:
When I encountered not only with my father's lack of  
understanding but also with his unwillingness to understand me as  
a parent, as far as things for which I (not he) have proves to be  
right are concerned.
label: anger

text: From the fact that my husband and I are not in good terms.
label: sad

text:
I felt joy when I saw my daughter after a separation of twenty  
days.
label: happy

text:
I felt fear when I sat for one of my exams. Though my fear was  
not quite justifiable, I still remember about it.
label: fear

text:
I thought him a good friend but he tried to lie to me several times.  
Last time was the height of impudence. He promised he would come  
home but he didn't. I felt a sense of anger and insult.
label: anger

text: A fear of lack of personal powers.
label: fear

text:
At an undeserved attitude toward a man, when human personality is  
not treated decently.
label: anger

text: At an irrevocable loss (with respect to human relations).
label: sad

text: When I was admitted to the University.
label: happy

text:
Because of a conflict with my parents there was a possibility to  
interrupt my studies.
label: fear

text: I feel a strong anger when I am treated unjustly.
label: anger

text: At a prolonged separation with my family.
label: sad

text: The day when my son said for the first time "mummy".
label: happy

text: Before an exam in logics.
label: fear

text:
My husband and I were invited at the house of our nieghbours then  
we got an invitation on the part of my parents which we had to  
refuse. A a result they called me by words that provoked my  
anger.
label: anger

text:
My son lives in the country. I feel sadness when I see mothers  
having walks with their children.
label: sad

text:
The sense of joy comes to me always after a period of depression,  
as an organic feeling for an upsurge. I don't exclude the  
situative feeling but in this case the reason is not in me, it's  
out of me.
label: happy

text:
I bet that I would jump down from a window. I was sure that I  
would jump but before I did it I rather felt fear.
label: fear

text:
A honest "sliding" on the part of a girlfriend of mine.  
Terribly crossed I started breaking things and tearing books.
label: anger

text:
Alone I am coming back home in the night after the serial  
"explanation".
label: sad

text: My son was born.
label: happy

text: I had a car accident.
label: fear

text:
I was drawn up a statement for an infringement of the traffic  
ordinance. In fact I was innocent.
label: anger

text: I lost a close friend.
label: sad

text:
After 10 days of hard work and having suffered many changes I  
passed my last exam.
label: happy

text: Before going to the dentist.
label: fear

text:
When I am made to do things in which I see no sense and I waste  
my time. Some time ago I had to participate in a sociological  
investigation and then I got really angry.
label: anger

text:
When I feel I must be with somebody, to talk with somebody - but  
I am alone.
label: sad

text:
When I am with friends and I do what pleases me this often  
happenes.
label: happy

text:
When I have to go in for an exam and the examinor is a person  
with a whimsical character and unsteady requirements.
label: fear

text:
I unfairly got a low mark on an exam and I failed to win a grant,  
since then I don't have much confidence in myself at an exam.
label: anger

text: It happened that I was alone - with no contacts with friends.
label: sad

text:
I was happy when I understood that the girl I liked was in love  
with me.
label: happy

text: I am afraid before an exam or colloquium.
label: fear

text:
I get angry when my smaller brother misbehaves and talks with indecent  
words.
label: anger

text: When my dog was stolen.
label: sad

text: When I met with friends that I hadn't seen for a long time.
label: happy

text:
One evening a friend of mine was telling a fearful story, nobody  
took it seriously but I got frightened.
label: fear

text:
I got angry with a stranger in a train who behaved impertinently  
and immorally
label: anger

text: When I failed at the first entrance exam.
label: sad

text:
Six months ago when I got acquaintanced with a person whom I  
trusted infinitely and from whom I expected help and friendly  
feelings. With him I found much in common - in our views and in  
our fate.
label: happy

text:
Few days ago I really experienced fear. It was connected with  
unexpected actions on the part of a group of people. This evoked  
in me many negative emotions.
label: fear

text:
I always get angry when somebody deceives me, or tries to conceal  
his lie skilfully and this offends me even more.
label: anger

text:
Sadness - this is an emotion which I have felt very often  
recently. I can't remember a concrete example. I will describe my  
general impression from severl situations which evoked this  
feeling in me.
label: sad

text: When I was accepted as a student.
label: happy

text:
I was a bit frightened when it was found that there was something  
wrong with my liver. However it turned out that it was not  
serious and I need not worry.
label: fear

text:
With the girl whom I may be loved truly. When she refused to come  
with me to an occasion (she was from another town).
label: anger

text:
For the girl who halped me go on living and made me happy - when  
I don't see her even for two or three days.
label: sad

text:
I felt it when on duty in the hospital I understood that I was  
not afraid to face death, that I also helped a little to relieve  
the pains of a patient.
label: happy

text:
Fear overwhelmed me when right against the car I was in I saw  
another one, as if out of control of the driver.
label: fear

text:
I felt it when a girl who was dear to me lied to my face. I got  
angry with the fact that she knew I didn't believe her but she  
kept on telling lies.
label: anger

text: Sadness, no, I felt something much stronger when my father died.
label: sad

text: When I knew that my husband and I were going to have a child.
label: happy

text:
Two years ago I saw a film on the TV. Even now it makes me  
afraid.
label: fear

text: When my husband stays late at a meeting and I have to be alone.
label: anger

text: The loss of a person I loved very much.
label: sad

text:
I was very happy when I got the message that I had been accepted  
as a student in medicine.
label: happy

text:
I felt something close to that when I saw that there was a man on  
the terrace of the flat.
label: fear

text:
I got angry when I learned how short a time we had to prepare for  
the term examinations.
label: anger

text:
I felt sad when my first boyfriend and I left each other. It was neither  
his fault nor mine.
label: sad

text:
When I learned that my parents were going abroad and leaving me  
alone for a few years.
label: happy

text:
I was at the seaside and my brother disappeared for a couple of  
hours.
label: fear

text:
When I was admitted to the Institute. I had problems with many  
people about my applying for this institute and I decided to  
prove that one can pass excellently without visiting any  
preparatory couse. That is - I proved what I could do on my own.
label: happy

text:
Once as a child I dreamed of a fire. Since that time I hadn't  
wanted to sleep in that bed and had feared the night darkness  
(and so it is now).
label: fear

text:
A chief was unjustly punished on an autumn brigade and the one  
who was really guilty kept silent. I stepped in front and told  
the truth. The guilty chief called me in after the roll-call and  
threatened me.
label: anger

text:
Years ago I fell in love for the first time. as natural for every  
school-girl I was day-dreaming. Later (after 3 years) we left  
each other. No one was to blame but I felt deep sadness. Even now  
I remember about it quite often.
label: sad

text:
When I learned I was admitted to study what I wanted most -  
floriculture (this is a narrow specialization from the general  
one).
label: happy

text:
I was walking on the pavement when a white car rolled on it and  
directed towards me. I was quite near the house wall when it  
rolled by and hit me.
label: fear

text:
My grandmother's brother had taken active part in the resistance  
movement. He had been in prison many times and there he lost his  
health. He became an invalid. When we phoned to First Aid the  
nurse on duty behaved quite unkindly when she understood how old  
he was (79).
label: anger

text:
My boyfriend is a soldier. He was on a leave. I felt sad when we  
had to get separated again.
label: sad

text:
I was very glad when I learned I was a student already. I heard  
about it over the phone, I didn't believe it at first.
label: happy

text: I had worries about a certain illness.
label: fear

text:
I suffered from a gynaecological illness. I was quite displeased  
to hear that my roommates had talked about it and they had  
misrepresented the truth. I felt deeply hurt when I learned that  
it was done by a "good" acquaintance of mine.
label: anger

text:
When my first boyfriend left me. I tried not to let him  
understand I felt miserable.
label: sad

text:
I felt glad when I took the rather difficult organic chemistry  
examination.
label: happy

text:
This was what I felt when my boyfriend went to Bourgas to study  
there. I had the feeling I would lose him. Anyway the distance  
Plovdiv-Bourgas seemed to me so great.
label: fear

text:
I confronted with this feeling at the Institute quite recently,  
the pedology lecturer was the cause.
label: anger

text:
This feeling was quite deep when my friend (girl) died in a car  
accident.
label: sad

text:
I sensed a strong feeling of joy when in the plant, at my working  
place, I got a message that I was admitted as full time student at  
the Higher Agricultural Institute.
label: happy

text:
Fear when fulfilling my obligations on my first night fatigue  
duty as a soldier.
label: fear

text:
When on a car journey a fellow student crossed our way with his  
own car and we had to bump into a roadside trunk.
label: anger

text: The loss of a close relative who was ill with cancer.
label: sad

text:
After a difficult exam. When I had not hoped to take it and had  
got a high mark. When you present someone with something and he  
feels glad.
label: happy

text:
Fear from the unknown. I felt fear when I sat for the entrance  
examinations.
label: fear

text:
I feel angry at people's indifference at our ability to be  
present at an event and to stay partial to what happens.
label: anger

text:
When you are far away from relatives and friends. I feel sad for  
my early years, for the freedom and the carefree years of  
childhood.
label: sad

text:
I was sitting for an exam in biochemistry, I was very excited  
because it was a supplementary examination. I passed the exam  
very well and was glad because I recovered my selfconfidence.
label: happy

text:
Students fear many things but we seem to fear the examinations  
most of all. I remember I was horror stricken before my  
microbiology exam, because it was a decisive one.
label: fear

text:
It was necessary to organise a competition in connection with a  
celebration. Everyone was to be present at that event. It turned  
out that there was no audience at all because everyone had  
pretended to be very intelligent and no one had come. I got  
furious.
label: anger

text:
When I part with my friends I feel always sad for some time. I  
can't remember a concrete example now. For example I have just  
parted with a friend of mine and I am feeling sad.
label: sad

text:
When I succeded in establishing a contact with a girl (who is now  
my girlfriend).
label: happy

text: I fear before each exam.
label: fear

text: When my bosom friend tried to lie to me.
label: anger

text: When I quarrelled with a very close friend of mine.
label: sad

text:
I feel joy usually after each taken exam, the last one was in  
February.
label: happy

text:
It was not long ago when I and two of friends of mine got quite drunk  
and one of them began to rave under the influence of the alcohol.  
I felt fear of what could have happened.
label: fear

text:
I felt anger at my last exam, I felt angry with our teacher,  
because he did not rate me objectively and I failed.
label: anger

text:
I met a girl some time ago and I cared very much about her but it  
happened so that we left each other. I felt some sort of sadness, I think  
I can call it so.
label: sad

text: When I was admitted to the Higher Institute.
label: happy

text:
I felt fear when I fell down and broke my leg into pieces and I  
could not feel it at all.
label: fear

text:
I felt angry when I failed in an exam about which I knew quite a  
few things and I did not deserve to be plucked.
label: anger

text:
When my mother and father were on an excursion in Chechoslovakia  
and I was at a student camp and I heard over the radio about the  
events that were taking place there.
label: sad

text:
I felt joy when I was admitted to the Higher Agricultural  
Institute.
label: happy

text:
I feel fear quite often but this feeling was very strong last  
year when my husband was quite unexpectedly sent to the hospital.
label: fear

text:
That was what I felt with a teacher who put down quite unreal  
marks.
label: anger

text:
I felt sad when a friend of mine died and I felt that something  
had irrevocably gone away from me.
label: sad

text:
I was for the first time on a brigade this year. At that time my  
sister was to bear a child. I was mad with joy when I opened the  
telegram from my parents and learned I had a nephew.
label: happy

text:
It was some years ago when one evening some people came home and  
told us my father was badly injured in an accident.
label: fear

text:
I faced this feeling when I realized I wasn't admitted to the  
institute in the first classifying, in spite of the high mark I  
had got at the entrance examination.
label: anger

text:
Always when I get separated from my friends and relatives from my  
home town.
label: sad

text:
Naturally when I got myself discharged this was my second  
birthday.
label: happy

text: When I failed my first exam at the Higher Institute.
label: fear

text:
A nuisance used to live in our flat a month ago. I experienced  
this feeling when I tried to chase her out.
label: anger

text: After my father's death.
label: sad

text:
I felt the greatest burst of joy when after being heavily ill for  
a long period, my father came back home.
label: happy

text:
I was terrified during an axcursion in Italy. I was lost and left  
alone in this unfamiliar country.
label: fear

text:
I took part in a football match. The referee was extremely  
partial to the opposite team. This stirred up my discontent and  
anger.
label: anger

text: When my first girlfriend an I left each other.
label: sad

text:
When I got a message that I was employed as a nurse at a  
kindergarten.
label: happy

text: When I first sat for an entrance examination.
label: fear

text:
When a teacher though pretending to be a highly cultivated  
teacher and a man, slapped a classmate of mine in the face quite  
undeservedly.
label: anger

text: When I got separated from my first love.
label: sad

text:
Being invited out by a person I wished to get closer to. He  
telephoned and invited me to go out with him the next night.
label: happy

text: Watching a horror movie with friends.
label: fear

text:
The breakup of a relationship. After the event I was upset/sad  
then angry maybe 2/3 weeks later.
label: anger

text:
The funeral of a friend who was killed in a car accident. She was  
of my own age, there were many of my own friends present, as well  
as her family etc.
label: sad

text:
Achievement of a task by a friend who had begun a new job. She  
wasn't confident of handling the situation so was thinking  of  
leaving the job only after 2 days employment.
label: happy

text:
Walking home at night after university - part of the way, there  
are ano lights and I am walking down a thoroughfare with the  
thouth of no one hearing me if I have to scream.
label: fear

text:
When my son omits to carry out certain duties at home that he  
knows needs doing.
label: anger

text:
When I saw my niece (5 yrs) crying in the hallway for her mother  
who had passed away about a month ago.
label: sad

text:
Felt joy a few years ago when I was away on holiday. And sat very  
close to my best friend looking straight into the eyes.
label: happy

text:
I had to tell someone that I was interested in remaining celibate  
and alone. And that my spiritual master strictly prohibited  
sexual relations outside of marriage. This caused great fear  
through lack of conviction afraid to hurt someone's feelings  
despite my own being hurt in the process.
label: fear

text:
In a sociology class I felt very angry towards some members of  
society for exploiting the Polynesian people, dawn raids by  
Police (Martin Luther King, Blacks in S.A.). But this was just a  
reflection of my own shortcomings.
label: anger

text:
Felt sad about some street kids in QUEII square, Aotea square.  
Because they had been sniffing glue and some were very young. I  
went into the role of a performing clown.
label: sad

text:
When I meet old past pupils of mine - and find they are all doing  
well - I feel joy. Yesterday I met a young woman (20 yrs) I'd  
taught her at 6 yrs, then at 12 yrs and hadn't seen her for last  
3-4 yrs; she was no longer a waitress but a meter maid for  
Council.
label: happy

text:
A Maori language oral test, yeaterday - Although I had studied  
intensely - once in the examiners room "I blew it" -  I was so  
nervous I couldn't reply easily - It was very important, but I  
got only blankness.
label: fear

text:
A friend visited and made comments that my house/garden were not  
as neat/tidy as in the past. I'd not seen her a year - She  
implied I'd gone to the pack (I'd only been working full time,  
and taking 3 University exams part time).
label: anger

text:
When my father a 4th/5th generation colonial (from Eng.) attacked  
me verbally about my chosen partner. A man whom he discarded  
because his colour skin was not white. His ultimate disgust  
saddned me.
label: sad

text: My 3 children - each top his class in the final exams 1984.
label: happy

text:
A truck (big one) nearly mowed me off the road (I was driving a  
small Lazer).
label: fear

text:
A shop in Downtown wouldn't accept my Visa Card - before December  
last year.
label: anger

text:
My dog of 16 and 1/2 years - "Lord Grey" died in his sleep - His  
death caused me more and deeper sadness than I thought.
label: sad

text: When my daughter was born.
label: happy

text:
When my mother entered surgery for a quadruple heart bypass. I  
felt intense fear at the time she was actually wheeled away.
label: fear

text:
When my husband got picked up in our new car for drunken driving.  
We had made a pact the other would not drink and so therefore  
would be the driver for the evening etc. I was not present at the  
time.
label: anger

text: When my grandmother died very suddenly without warning.
label: sad

text:
Being reunited with my family after not having seen them for 5  
years, at the airport. Sheer elation at getting through the  
"paper work" collecting bags and the anticipation of coming  
through the customs gate.
label: happy

text:
I caught a huge eel on a fishing line which I had pulled into the  
boat. I cut the line and threw the whole lot back into the water.  
Later that day and about ten miles away I went swimming and  
someone made the comment wondering how far eels could swim, I  
abruptly ended swimming for fear at an unseen eel for a few days  
until we had left the district.
label: fear

text:
My partner without discussing with me the situation decided it  
was time for us to have a break and went ahead and arranged his  
own life for the next 6-12 months, then told me the day before it  
was about to happen having been tolerant and friendly for the  
preceding week.
label: anger

text:
I had been living in an overseas city and made the decision to  
leave the city and come home about 12 months before I met a whole  
new set of friends, leaving them at the airport was sad and  
traumatic as they had helped me in many ways and I knew I  
wouldn't see many of them again.
label: sad

text:
After I had managed to fail my first year at University I was  
scared as to what I was going to do with my future. I didn't want  
a mundane 9-5 job and yet I didn't know if I could pay my way  
through an unsubsidized year at university to settle down and  
continue my studies.
label: fear

text:
This situation keeps occurring - when my little sister disagrees  
with me or vice-versa. We have very similar temperaments and I  
always end up feeling angry at her and myself for fighting so  
much over unimportant trivial matters.
label: anger

text:
When my grandmother, who has been living with us for 14 years,  
had a stroke and was left paralysed on one side. She has been  
quite close to our family and to see her suffer in this way makes  
me feel really sad.
label: sad

text:
My mother along with some of my friends gave me a surprise  
birthday party - they invited a large number of my friends along  
too.
label: happy

text:
My mother did not come home till late at night (Ages ago). Anyway  
if I don't know where my parents are and when they'll be back I  
start thinking that perhaps they have had an accident and are  
perhaps dead.
label: fear

text:
Because I am the Captain of a basketball team I usually organise  
a roster system so that everyone in the team can have a turn at  
doing either a duty or a ref. A lot of the time the girls can't  
be bothered or just forget - I usually have to fill in.
label: anger

text:
So as to be closer to the university I have left home and moved  
into Auckland. It now seems as if I have left home - especially  
my family - forever.
label: sad

text:
Passing my pharmacy exams which meant my tertiary education for  
pharmacy completed.
label: happy

text:
When I was in a car with my parents and friends and we had to  
back up (reverse) pass a river which when I recall it (I was only  
about 5 yrs) seemed we were going to fall in and drown.
label: fear

text:
When my boyfriend wouldn't dance with me on my graduation night  
because he thought I could dance with my friends who were  
friendly.
label: anger

text:
When my sister (really my niece) died of cancer at the age of 2  
yrs after I took her to the doctor at the age of 1 and he  
diagnosed it.
label: sad

text:
Joy for me is when all my family gather around home for special  
occasions as Christmas etc. It really gives me joy to see my  
family and relatives and to observe natures productivity process  
which have been going on for centuries.
label: happy

text:
I had this experience of fear when few people were fighting at a  
social one night, which one of my relative was involved. My fear  
was greatly for him because he was being assaulted badly.
label: fear

text: Never really had the experience just yet - N/A.
label: anger

text:
This occurred when my girlfriend and I have to finish our  
relationship due to some circumstances between her and her  
family. I was really sad, hurt and couldn't really find any  
reason why am I still living. Is this life is all about ? This  
was one of few question which crept up vividly every time I  
thought about what had happened.
label: sad

text: Letting Jesus take control of my emotions i.e., ill feeling.
label: happy

text: Had fear of losing husband.
label: fear

text:
When present boyfriend's mother approached my parents and self -  
to leave her son alone - as she did not want me for a future  
daughter-in-law.
label: anger

text: When boyfriend could not stand up to his mother or for himself.
label: sad

text:
My cousin asked me to be a bridesmaid for her. This made really  
happy because I was adopted into the family and her asking me  
made me realise that she saw me as a cousin and not just another  
person. There were other cousins she could have asked but she  
asked me.
label: happy

text:
That if ever I was really naughty I would be sent away from my  
Mum and Dad to another family. I was fostered from age 5 and  
didn't get to Mum and Dad until I was 6 and then legally adopted  
at 14.
label: fear

text:
(1) My father died. (2) My natural father contacted me a year  
after my father died and this angered me more as I thought he  
should be dead and not my father.
label: anger

text:
My father died. I was away at the time and did not know until two  
days after.
label: sad

text: Joy at meeting a woman I love very much.
label: happy

text: When approached by a gang of youths in town at night.
label: fear

text:
When a man, a stranger to me, personally insulted a close woman  
friend of mine in public.
label: anger

text: After my father died suddenly of a heart attack.
label: sad

text:
When my lover and I felt like we had gone full circle. And our  
relationship was new, fresh, vital etc. once again.
label: happy

text:
My daughter was 2 yrs she went up to a colt tried to hit it. It  
turned on her and kicked her over the heart, sent her flying  
through the air. I left my mother and sister to deal to her as  
they are nurses. I felt I didn't want to know if she was going to  
die, it was just too much.
label: fear

text: My anger is with men, their inability to be human (not all men).
label: anger

text:
The saddest I've ever been was when my lover was killed,  
hitch-hiking to work.
label: sad

text:
A good friend, the wife of the vicar of my church came up to me  
from the pews (I am in the choir) and shook my hand during the  
time for an informal "greeting" in the church service. She said a  
few words.
label: happy

text:
I walked up the main street of Auckland at 10 o'clock at night. I  
expected it to be very active with people, gangs, fast cars etc,  
thought it was actually quite quiet, though also oppressive. I  
walked about half a mile and bought a drink along the way.
label: fear

text:
Someone in my family (my brother I suspected) ate a bun which I  
had made for myself. It was during a long telephone call after I  
had just made it and put it in the oven warming drawer.
label: anger

text:
Sitting in a bus, I heard behind, the voice of a girl I was  
friendly with. After her talking for some time with another girl  
I decided it wasn't her in fact that someone miming her, which it  
was when I finally looked. I was talking to a friend at the time.
label: sad

text:
My friend replying to my letter and again saying he was attracted  
to me and suggesting we write, talk and get together and see how  
things went and his suggestion that I could ring and doing that it  
was really good - though really insane conversation.
label: happy

text:
Being sexually assaulted (not rape, but passionate kissing) by a  
friend's father - he stopped when he was driving me home. I  
hadn't wanted the lift, had refused 3 times, and then felt it'd  
be rude to refuse again. Was really afraid of what he might do.
label: fear

text:
I live by myself and a few weeks ago was woke by a man on the end  
of my bed coming up my bed at me. I was really angry, told him to  
get out. He was surprised, hesitated; I started to move towards  
him and he backed off - kept telling him - loudly, but firmly to  
go. Because I'd got the initiative, I succeeded. A very powerful  
message.
label: anger

text:
When my grandmother died - I wasn't sad so much that she'd died  
because she was old, but because she lived in the last few years  
in an old people's home and had nothing very much that was hers -  
no chair, or private space, and when I went to visit she would be  
sitting in the "lliving" room the TV room. It was hopeless. And I  
felt awkward so I didn't go and I was sad 'cos how I couldn't.
label: sad

text:
When during a social evening with my father, brother, sister,  
close friend and my father's 2nd wife - I had an argument with my  
father, who abused my friend who was sticking up for me.
label: anger

text:
When the girl whom I have lusted after expressed reciprocal  
feelings and then days later changed her mind.
label: sad

text:
Girlfriend arriving back from overseas and picking her up from  
airport. When she finally appeared from customs and we came in  
contact again.
label: happy

text:
Fear of punishment for having broken an item of value to my  
parents.
label: fear

text:
That a friend had been badly beaten and stabbed many times and  
the person that did it got away without any punishment from the  
law.
label: anger

text: The death of an animal we had reared.
label: sad

text:
The feeling of joy when again I had confessed my sin and  
experienced God's forgiving grace and cleansing power - total  
enlightenment and freedome - bliss.
label: happy

text:
Riding through a bush fire on an island of Australia - on a  
pushbike as a little boy - all alone, lost and surrounded by  
smouldering wood and flame.
label: fear

text:
When bicycling along, a courier van started to tail me very close  
- I sped up and moved over and he just did the same. I reacted  
violently, much physical responding in the dangerous situation.
label: anger

text:
My cat was sick and I had to take him to the vet to be put down -  
no one else there to do it.
label: sad

text:
First time I slept with my present girlfriend. Had been best  
friends for a year but had been hesitant about getting involved  
emotionally.
label: happy

text:
Waiting for a taxi - when within 1/2 an hour two separate people  
challenged me to fight for no apparent reason except they were  
drunk.
label: fear

text:
Deliberately provoked by someone close. Angered by the  
deliberation not the provocation.
label: anger

text:
My girlfriend let me down badly 3 times in one week. These  
instances summed up all the negative aspects of our relationship  
which at the time seemed doomed to fail.
label: sad

text:
Hearing that I had been successful in getting a position whereby  
my financial, physical, spiritual and emotional needs will be  
well catered for. This position fulfils a lot of my aims for the  
last five years of my life.
label: happy

text:
When I decided to leave my steady, secure employment to come to  
university. Because I didn't know if I could cope with all the  
requirements of study and also being older I didn't know if I  
would enjoy mixing with younger people, also financial  
insecurity.
label: fear

text:
When a close friend failed to live up to the expectations I had  
of him - thereby causing pain to his spouse. I believe that my  
anger was probably a reaction of fear that I wouldn't be able to  
live up to my own expectations.
label: anger

text:
Departure of a very close friend - for a long stay overseas,  
sharing in the sorrow of her parents who were left behind.
label: sad

text: Hearing Fran Wilde introduce the Bill.
label: happy

text:
Being harrassed for being gay; suggestions of being physically  
beaten - acting as informal bouncer in a gay bar.
label: fear

text: Landlord putting up rents sneakly and slimily.
label: anger

text:
Listening and watching a tape of someone with AIDS being  
prejudiced against at a counselling course on AIDS with 20  
others.
label: sad

text: Won a prize for effort.
label: happy

text: Assaulted by drunken neighbour.
label: fear

text:
I was playing in a football tournament and saw the rules openly  
disregarded.
label: anger

text: Death of brother.
label: sad

text:
I was feeling really low - had been a series of fights with my  
siblings, been under pressure at school and wasn't going to the  
party I wanted to go - instead I was going out with my family. A  
guy called and said, in effect, that I was "nice" and he liked  
me. Hence the emotional joy.
label: happy

text:
I was watching a movie alone - it was a horror movie. The music  
was a deep pulsing type - not really music. And a light flashed  
on and off. It was in the complete darkness of a movie theatre  
that was almost empty.
label: fear

text:
My sister and I were fighting as usual. She's older tham I am,  
bigger built and stronger I couldn't win in a physical battle and  
in a verbal battle I couldn't seem to get through to her to  
really hurt her.
label: anger

text:
My paternal grandmother had died. We weren't close but she was  
blood. I didn't cry but I was sad, partly due to her death and  
partly I think, due to the fact that I couldn't/didn't cry.
label: sad

text:
Winning a rowing race at a Karapiro regatta. With 7 other  
friends.
label: happy

text:
Being alone in Europe and having to catch a train and bus to the  
airport, then board the plane alone.
label: fear

text:
At school teacher for not allowing us to go out on New Year's Eve  
when on a class trip overseas.
label: anger

text:
I was in a car accident on the way back from a weekend rowing  
regatta we'd won. 5 others were in the car. I thought I'd never  
be able to row again.
label: sad

text:
When I won a position on the track-team for the trans-tasman  
games when I was eleven.
label: happy

text: When I was jumped by three men in a deserted area.
label: fear

text:
Once a person in authority (school teacher) was telling blatant  
lies about me and the headmistress would not let me defend  
myself. She was also telling lies about other members of my  
family.
label: anger

text: When my mother died.
label: sad

text: Easter holiday - I had been working weekends and had just left.
label: happy

text: Haven't been frightened for ages.
label: fear

text:
I visited a special education school. The headmaster applied a  
policy of strict positive - negative reinforcement to the  
children involved. Children who measured up to his standards were  
made a fuss of - children who didn't were ignored.
label: anger

text:
I felt sad with the two situations I described before. The cat  
and the school. Sadness was intermingled with the other feelings.
label: sad

text:
Getting my kitten, found at work several years ago, taking him  
home in a box on my motorbike, showing it to my defacto.
label: happy

text: Obscene phone call where the person knew my name.
label: fear

text: At work being shifted to another area.
label: anger

text:
Enrolling at varsity, being told I couldn't get in to certain  
papers.
label: sad

text:
When I was finally able to return to a job that I enjoyed doing  
after several months absence (I was not needed during this time).
label: happy

text: When I was attacked by a teenage boy and had my wallet stolen.
label: fear

text:
Someone who was speeding was forced to slow down when I pulled  
out onto the road and proceeded to abuse me at the next set of

label: anger

text:
When someone I was close to became a paranoid schizophrenic and I

label: sad

text:
At my wedding - standing with the man I love and acknowledging  
that fact to members of family and friends.
label: happy

text:
As a result of breaking the indicator light as mentioned  
for guilt.
label: fear

text:
Arriving home from work after a long and tiring day to find no

label: anger

text:
At the death of my husband's father's mother which occurred  
during university examinations and therefore I was unable to  
attend her funeral.
label: sad

text: Waking in morning (early morning) and having whole day to myself.
label: happy

text:
Being driven by friend who suddenly swerved and skidded a little.  
It was night and on a long trip. We ended up on side of road.
label: fear

text:
Friend (male) hinted that my talking to other men at a pub was

the entire evening.
label: anger

text: On rising. No apparent reason.
label: sad

text: When my first niece was born.
label: happy

text:
In a flat in Sydney - rough area at home on my own - the flat had

label: fear

text: When the bus driver failed to stop and pick me up at a bus stop.
label: anger

text: When my uncle died of leukemia at age 35.
label: sad

text:
When I went to the pub with a large group of friends, we drank  
and danced.
label: happy

text: Watched a horror movie which involved sexual attacks on women.
label: fear

text:
My boyfriend promised to take me to see a game of tennis and rang  
saying he was going to the pub with some of his friends instead.
label: anger

text:
My mother was unwell and went for many cancer tests. She spent

label: sad

text: Birth of children.
label: happy

text: Being alone at night.
label: fear

text: In a hurry to get to lectures and the car would not start.
label: anger

text: When grandfather died.
label: sad

label: happy

text:
Stopped at lights in Mangere late one Friday night on way home

started banging and shaking it. Light was red and had nowhere to  
go until light changed. When green I took off.
label: fear

text:
When fired unjustly from a job as casual bar-person. Charged with  
giving away free drinks. Not done so and had witnesses to prove

label: anger

text:
Close friend leave to go overseas for an indefinite period.  
Farewell scene at airport.
label: sad

text:
Receiving understanding from within self of a subject I had

label: happy

text:
To talk in a meeting - expound my thoughts on a subject. Fear  
delayed me acting to do this.
label: fear

text:
Towards wife's laziness in not performing her usual duties  
because of television watching.
label: anger

text: Watching suffering in Third World country.
label: sad

text:
Meeting best friend at the airport (boyfriend) who I had missed  
terribly.
label: happy

text:
Confronted outside a party by some very nasty character -  
gesturing to a car full of mean-acting friends - felt in danger.
label: fear

text: NO RESPONSE.
label: anger

text: My cat died painfully and slowly.
label: sad

text:
I was very pleased and happy when my older sister came home from  
living somewhere out of town and I hadn't seen her for months. We  
are very close sisters.
label: happy

text:
I was skiing alone and the mountain became covered with mist and  
I thought I was lost and was going to panic.
label: fear

text:
My parents didn't allow me to go to a social function that all my  
friends were attending.
label: anger

text:
While still at school a friend died of cancer, after being ill  
for a long time, she was 17 yrs old.
label: sad

text:
When my brother who has been out of New Zealand for 10 years came  
to visit with his wife which none of our family had previously  
met.
label: happy

text:
When I had to give a speech about some historical event, to an  
audiece of about 200 people my own age whom I did not know.
label: fear

text:
In arguments with a close friend or relative where my point of  
view is completely disregarded.
label: anger

text:
When my grandfather whom I had met only once for 3 weeks, died  
after several months. I was really sad because he was a lovely  
person and I did not have the means for his company.
label: sad

text:
When my former boyfriend and I reconciled and he decided that I  
was very important to him. I had always wanted us to get back  
together again, but had doubted the likelihood of this, so I was  
very happy when my small amount of faith was vindicated.
label: happy

text:
When riding in a very fastly-driven car on a lose metal road at a  
very late hour - no other cars on road, and driver was taking  
corners very sharply. I felt afraid - because if an accident  
happened, the area was very isolated. Also, I feared for driver,  
after I was dropped off - would he make it home safely.
label: fear

text:
When at very short notice I agreed to work in place of a friend  
who was sick, and owner of the restaurant refused to allow me a  
drink later in the evening (which is usually always available for  
workers), did not thank me, and was generally indifferent towards  
me - I felt I did not deserve this.
label: anger

text:
When I learned that my former boyfriend had become engaged -  
although I was glad that he had found what he wanted, I was very  
sad at my own personal loss, since I had always hoped we might  
one day reconcile.
label: sad

text:
I did a solo flight from Ardmore to Kaikohe before I got my pilot  
licence. I can remember it was gorgeous day and I was on a  
natural high, cruising up the coast with my maps and compasses  
and gear. Other pilots had seen me off and wished me good luck  
and it was a real adventure.
label: happy

text:
A friend (female) and I were on holiday on Great Barrier Island  
by ourselves. One night we were nearly raped by about 20 locals -  
they came to our bach and tried to break the doors down. All of  
them were stoned or drunk and we hid under the bunks and were  
totally terrified. Eventually these guys gave up and went looking  
for us on the beach. We escaped and slept in the bush for 2  
nights.
label: fear

text:
I "cooked" the engine in my father's car - it was actually his  
fault because he hadn't fixed the temperature gauge or told me.  
When I finally got home I was absolutely screamed at and the  
anger I experienced was over the injustice of it all plus the  
huge row which developed.
label: anger

text:
This sounds really predictable and usual but it was absolutely  
heart-rending at the time. My first lover (I was 15) just rang up  
one day and announced that he had found another woman. I never  
saw him again and it hurt because I was positive that it was  
"TRUE LOVE" !!
label: sad

text:
A holiday at a whitesand deserted beach. A cool evening near the  
end of summer and we had a fire in the sand - toasted  
marshmellows, cuddled and drank champagne.
label: happy

text:
Skiing down a very icy slope, very fast in white-out conditions.  
Out of control with no idea of what I was doing or where I was  
heading.
label: fear

text:
My best friend at school told lies about me to a boy I was seeing  
and went out with him herself.
label: anger

text:
I found a baby opposum on the road and took it home and cared for  
it for a week. It had to be force-fed and carried in a fur pouch  
under my jersey. My father had the vet put it to sleep as he said  
they carried diseases.
label: sad

text:
Winning a race that I had been training for, for many weeks.  
(Running Race).
label: happy

text:
When I was very young and we moved as a family to Auckland from

label: fear

text:
When someone ignores what I am saying or doesn't let me have my

label: anger

text:
When I got into an argument with someone and was very abusive,

label: sad

text:
Listening to the opening bars of Tchaikovsdy's symphony No.2

label: happy

text:
As a passenger in a vehicle travelling from the steep side of

label: fear

text: As in sadness (A), relating to this slaghter of fur-seals.
label: anger

text:
A) A documentary in which baby fur seals were being

B) Description of a disfigured orphaned child in Hiroshima

label: sad

text:
Seeing my sister after about 2 years of not seeing her. Only

label: happy

text:
I imagined I heard footsteps up the hall while sleeping in bed

label: fear

text:
Stopped at a Fast Food shop with friends and a few locals wanted

label: anger

text:
My father recently having a heart attack - spending a few months

label: sad

text: Talking with someone I admire a lot.
label: happy

Came back from surfing to find car broken into and gear and money

text: Caused a family disturbance.
label: sad

text:
Social situation - at the pub - a close friend of 2 years told

Brother continually interupting while I was talking on the

Almost crashing into the back of a car while driving along the

text:
A person I really like left for overseas for a few months, I had

label: sad

text:
When I received my U.E. accredited as I was totally unexpecting

label: happy

text:
I went to see a movie and I went with a friend, it was really

label: fear

text:
When my flatmate put me down because she "thought" she was better

text:

text:

label: fear

text:
I lent a text-book to a person I did not know very well, they

At the beginning of the year I moved to a new city - I felt sad

Getting University Entrance accredited and arriving home from

text:

text:

label: anger

text:
At my grandfather's funeral - My grandparents virtually raised me

A large german shepherd dog ran and barked at me (he didn't bite

Most recently when the chairman at the New Zeeland Rugby Union

label: sad

text:
I was biking with my boyfriend, the sun shining after a long

label: happy

text:
In a discussion the leader wanted to stop because she was of the

text:
Sleeping alone in a tent, while hearing several noises such as

label: fear

 Before going in to see it I was afraid as it was the first time

 I saw her in a discotheque.  We do not like discotheques but we
