I was angry when my sister began to talk nonsense and to laugh at  
the way I swept the room.  My anger grew (I tried to control  
myself).  After telling her to leave me alone, I vented my anger  
on her as she did not obey me.
label: anger

text:
My mother was working with a knife and we were all laughing  
heartily.  She was not able to control the knife and stuck it  
deep into her hand.
label: sad

text:
A friend of mine suggested that I become a film extra.  The idea  
seemed very funny to me and my reaction seemed rather outlandish  
to the others.
label: happy

text:
One day I went to the cinema to see a film in which I was  
interested.  On arriving there I saw a long queue (which I had  
not expected) and went back home without seeing the film.
label: fear

text:
When I miss the train and I am late, and I have to wait half an  
hour for the next one.
label: anger

text: When I knew I had to go out with my mother on some errands.
label: sad

text:
When they phoned me from Great-Britain to tell me that I could go  
there, if I wished, in Summer.
label: happy

text: When I was operated on the knee and had to go through rehabilitation.
label: fear

text:
In a very important basket-ball match where a lot was at stake, I  
played very badly.
label: anger

text:
When a friend of mine told me that he was going to commit  
suicide.
label: sad

text:
When I passed my driving test, as it was the fifth time that I  
had taken this test.
label: happy

text: When my mother was robbed in a shop.
label: fear

text:
I was given an exam which I thought did not measure at all my  
ability or my knowledge of the subject.
label: anger

text:
When I saw the film "Johnny got his gun" which deals with the  
consequences of the Vietnam war.
label: sad

text: When I passed the university entrance exam.
label: happy

text:
One night, while I was sleeping, I woke up suddenly with the  
sensation that there was someone in my room.
label: fear

text: When my brother was held up and robbed.
label: anger

text: When they told me that my grandfather was rather ill.
label: sad

text:
I came across a friend with whom I had lost touch for a long  
time.
label: happy

text:
I had decided to propose to the man I liked to make a trip  
together.  One day, during breakfast I told him my idea.  I was  
afraid of his not accepting it and that the idea would end up as  
a failure.
label: fear

text:
A person I trusted a lot gave me many false explanations to  
justify a wrong action.
label: anger

text:
I was having breakfast with a classmate and suddenly I began to  
cry as I thought of a friend of mine whom I had not seen for a  
long time.
label: sad

text:
At a party, on New Year's Eve, I met on old friend whom I had not  
seen for some time
label: happy

text:
Once I failed seven subjects at school and I was terrified to  
give my report card to my father.  I left it on the table and went to  
bed very early in order to avoid him seeing me.
label: fear

text:
When, after drinking a glass of water, I found a cockroach walking  
out of the glass.
label: anger

text:
I have a very close friend who lives in another city and we have  
been writing to each other for a long time.  The last time I went  
to her city, just to see her, I was disappointed to see how great  
the distance between us was.
label: sad

text:
Every time, in the last few days, when my girlfriend told me that  
she loves me.
label: happy

text:
I stayed alone in the dark at night in the mountain, waiting for  
my uncle.  I remember that I took a big stone and it calmed me.
label: fear

text:
We were at school, in the room for audiovisual classes.  We were  
watching a film, and just behind me two classmates were bothering  
me with their mocking and shoves.  I reacted angrily (I suppose)   
by hitting one of them.
label: anger

text:
[ During a summer holiday a French girl and I had becoe back  
home, I felt very sad.]
label: sad

text: A party I went to last Christmas.
label: happy

text: When my mother had a nervous illness.
label: fear

text: During my last exam.
label: anger

text: When I had to come back from my village last Christmas.
label: sad

text: When I knew the feelings of a beloved person.
label: happy

text: A fall during a climb, with almost with no previous experience.
label: fear

text:
On the occasion of assignment of tasks and responsibilities in  
which such an assignment, dispropotionately carried with it high  
responsibility and low ability of organisation and resolution.
label: anger

text:
Moving to an unknown place, away from the familiar surroundings  
and into a situation of loneliness.
label: sad

text:
In a dark street at 4 o'clock in the night and there was  
complete silence.
label: fear

text:
When they broke the artistic work of several weeks.  Changes were  
made and it was broken without permission, they had no right to  
do this.
label: anger

text:
When the train taking me to my military service left the station,  
on the platform remained relatives, projects and goodtimes.  I  
had a hard year ahead.
label: sad

text:
I was talking to a friend and he said something which was very  
funny.
label: happy

text:
When I was young I saw a horror film.  Then when I went to sleep,  
the film came back too my mind and the characters frighteneed my  
imagination.
label: fear

text:
In a confrontation with a person, he provoked me several times  
till I reacted in an angry way.  Fortunately there were no  
disastrous consequences.
label: anger

text: I was watching a sad film and it affected me deeply.
label: sad

text:
When I knew that there were, at last, no problems in making a  
journey that I had been wanting to make for a long time.
label: happy

text: It was more that fear - anguish -that I felt before my last exam.
label: fear

text:
When I had an argument with my best friend and I thought that I  
was right and she was not.
label: anger

text:
When I realized that it was impossible for me to be as free as I  
had imagined and that I could not do anythong about it.
label: sad

text:
When a study tour got confirmed, I was happy all the time till     
the tour began.
label: happy

text:
I was walking down a road and suddenly a few dogs appeared at a fence  
and started barking angrily.  They were jumping and it seemed  
that they would come for me any time.
label: fear

text:
When I knew that they would not give me a transfer from one  
university to another.  I began to insult the educatioon  
authorities and the government, I ended up at the door.
label: anger

text:
We went to visit my mother at the residence.  She was crying and  
said that she was about to die.  I believed all her complaints  
and continously thought of the possibility of loosing her.
label: sad

text:
When I received my report card in C.O.U.  I was afraid of obtaining  
low marks, but they were much higher than expected.
label: happy

text:
I was at the cinema with my sister and her boyfriend.  A man  
sitting beside me started to stroke my leg for a while, he left in  
the middle of the film.
label: fear

text:
My father began to say incoherant things concerning my brother's and  
my own behaviour towards him.  His biased (authoritarian) and  
ridiculous point of view made us angry.
label: anger

text: I had failed some subjects in mathematics.
label: sad

text:
When I fell crazily in love with a beautiful girl and she returned  
my love.
label: happy

text:
When I was caught by the police and was kept with a group of  
delinquents, which added to my fear of being shut up.  I was  
afraid of the people near me and the future consequences.
label: fear

text:
When I was the target of a great many insults and completely  
unfair accusations of a large group of people.
label: anger

text: When my best friend died, at the age of 16.
label: sad

text:
When I came across an old friend whom I had not seen for a very  
long time.
label: happy

text:
I had an accident in which I hurt my eye.  I was afraid of having  
injured it badly.
label: fear

text: When I was accused of something I had not done.
label: anger

text: A close friend died.
label: sad

text:
I received an unexpected letter from a friend I had met a short  
time before.  He sent me a poem and wished me good luck.  I felt  
very happy because I had great esteem for that person.
label: happy

text:
I was walking with another person when a "gang" separted us and  
pushed me in to a house, hit me in the stomach and the face, then  
they left - leaving me bleeding.
label: fear

text:
A certain person started to say dreadful things very calmly, I  
felt hurt and disgusted.
label: anger

text:
A certain person whom I respect and esteem a lot pays me no  
attention.  She keeps up appearances but shows almost no interest  
in me.
label: sad

text:
When I received some good news : I obtained an amount of money I  
needed to buy something I had been planning to buy.
label: happy

text:
When my relatives and I were in a car going slowly on a frozen  
road.
label: fear

text:
My parents were having a typical family argument.  I came in and  
saw the scene and became angry.
label: anger

text: I was going away, leaving a dear person behind.
label: sad

text: When I talk to my friends.
label: happy

text: When I am walking on the streets and see a gang of thugs.
label: fear

text: When people harrass me I feel oppressed by their behavior.
label: anger

text: When I am with a friend and we have to leave each other.
label: sad

text:
[ Any situation in everyday life has this emotional sense, in  
class, in the street, at home, at the table..........]
label: happy

text:
On a dark night I felt that there were several people near me  
and I did not know who they were.
label: fear

text:
When I learned that several people had died in the street due to   
the cold weather.
label: anger

text:
When I saw in the newspapers, on the T.V, and magazines the  
chaotic situation caused by the drought and hunger in  
Mauritania.
label: sad

text:
One night, at a friend's place I realized that I had everything I  
most wished, around me.
label: happy

text:
During a demonstration I climbed up the closed central door of a  
bus.  When the bus stopped I had to go back to the same place,  
afraid that the police would see me.
label: fear

text:
When I saw parents punishing their little child for something he  
had not done.  In my opinion, even if he had done it he should  
not have been punished for it.
label: anger

text:
A friend of mine was hurt as he thought that our relationship was  
not the same as before and something had gone wrong.
label: sad

text:
When they told me that I had been admitted to the faculty of  
medicine.
label: happy

text: Almost always when I go to fetch the results of an exam.
label: fear

text: [ No description.]
label: anger

text:
When I decided not to out any longer with a girl whom I liked  
quite a lot.  This made me feel low for a some time.
label: sad

text: When I obtained good marks in a subject I had failed before.
label: happy

text: When a friend of mine told me a horror story.
label: fear

text:
I was with my family and we found some abandoned puppies.  I  
wanted to help them but everyone said no.  We then left.
label: anger

text: At my grandfather's death.
label: sad

text:
When I was told that they had got tickets for me for a film  
marathon I wanted to see.
label: happy

text:
We were on the road in a car when a lorry bypassed us.  We had to  
swerve and we almost got run over.
label: fear

text:
I had applied for a job and they had assured me that the exams  
would take place a few months later.  A week later I went to  
obtain some more information and they told me that the exams had  
already taken place.
label: anger

text:
I received a letter from some friends, who do not live in Madrid,  
telling me that they would not come on holiday.  I had arranged  
everythiing for them.
label: sad

text: The man I am going around with gave me a very special present.
label: happy

text:
I thought that I would be scolded for a comment I had made, which  
I should not have made.
label: fear

text:
My sister came back home and reproached me for not having tidied  
up the house, although I had been working all morning and she had  
done nothing.
label: anger

text:
At my grandfather's funeral.  I remembered that the thing he  
liked and respected most was earth, I thought that he had  
attained what he wanted and was not separated from it any longer.
label: sad

text:
When I saw a friend of mine, whom I had not seen for a long time  
and I had lost his address and telephone number.
label: happy

text:
I was in my village when a bull jumped over a fence and started  
chasing my friends and me.  We were very frightened till we  
climbed up a tree.
label: fear

text: When I saw a car run over a child, out of carelessness.
label: anger

text:
I failed a subject despite the fact that I had studied quite a  
lot for it.
label: sad

text:
I was spending the week-end with some friends.  We were waiting  
for another friend and we went to the meet him at the bus stop, a   
woman we met there told us that the coach had already left.  I  
was afraid that I would not see my friend, but at last we found  
him.
label: happy

text:
I was walking down a little village at night.  There was nobody  
in the steet.  A dog began to bark, I felt that it was following  
me.  Then I began to run, the other dogs started barking too.  At  
last I arrived home.
label: fear

text: My parents did not let me go on holidays with my friends.
label: anger

text: I was told that a friend of mine was going to Mexico for good.
label: sad

text:
I was on holidays, and I was going to meet a friend whom I had  
not seen for six months.  Again I felt very happy.
label: happy

text:
We were camping in the mountains, and a friend and I went for a  
walk.  It was getting darker and darker and we were not sure of  
the right way back.
label: fear

text:
I sent a book to a friend of mine.  The book meant a lot to me  
and he lost it.
label: anger

text: To say goodbye to dear friends after the holidays.
label: sad

text:
My sister in law was about to have a child, and there were some  
problems.  They had to do a Caesarean.  After a while, everything   
was all right.
label: happy

text: Waiting for my marks in a difficult subject.
label: fear

text:
I gave some personal information to a friend of mine, and he told  
it to some others who were implicated in the affair.
label: anger

text:
The holidays come to an end, and the next day we had to go back  
to University and to the exams.
label: sad

text:
Last course, when I passed with good marks three subjects which I had  
previously failed.
label: happy

text: I was attacked by a man at a bus stop at night.
label: fear

text:
My mother told me that I could not go to the mountains.  Despite  
my age, as long as I am in her house I must do what she says.
label: anger

text:
When my nephew was taken to hospital with meningitis and we did  
not know what would happen.
label: sad

text:
One evening, I was with a group of friends having a talk.  There  
was a very trustful and joyful atmosphere.
label: happy

text:
We were walking in the park at night.  It was very dark and very  
late.  We began to hear foot steps all around us, and we could  
not find our way out.
label: fear

text:
[ One day I arrived home rather tired and found the house..... In  
addition I was asked many questions which I did not want to  
answer.]
label: anger

text:
I was selected to do a rest for a foreign ballet but I did not  
have the money to do it.
label: sad

text:
It was Saturday, my duties were over for a few hours and I could  
at last be with the people I wanted to see.
label: happy

text:
One night, I was alone at home.  My fear was caused by some  
strange noises which put my imagination to work.
label: fear

text:
When I got to know about the reaction of a friend of mine in a  
certain situation.  I had not expected him to react that way.
label: anger

text:
I felt alone among a large number of people.  I was sad to see  
that nobody cared about what was happening to me.
label: sad

text:
I was going to my village, after having been rather oppressed in  
Madrid.
label: happy

text:
I was watching a procession during the Holy week, and a penitent  
approached me.
label: fear

text:
My mother read a letter that a friend of mine had written to me  
telling me how she had got drunk the last time.
label: anger

text:
Last Summer I achieved someting that I had been wanting for a  
long time.
label: happy

text:
I was in a camp and went out for a walk at night on my own.  I lost   
my way and spent several hours looking for the camp.
label: fear

text:
My parents scolded me a lot for something I had not done.  It was  
my sister who had done it.
label: anger

text:
When my brother was born, everything went all right.  It had been  
very likely that he would have a deficiency (my sister suffers  
from Down's Syndrome) and that my mother would be in danger.
label: happy

text:
When we got lost in Florence and the coach did not turn up until  
midnight.  I had no place to go to and there were strange reports  
at the police station.
label: fear

text:
When an English teacher unfairly made me repeat a semester which  
I thought I had passed.  I had to ask my parents for some more  
money to carry on studying.
label: anger

text:
The person whom I liked most left me for a friend of mine, after  
several months of mutual help and a profound knowledge of each  
other.
label: sad

text:
When I passed the university entrance exam.  I had thus finished  
with a difficult period of my life and I was about to begin one  
which I had desired a lot.
label: happy

text:
When I was at home alone, I felt a super-natural force, dangerous  
for me and the people close to me.
label: fear

text:
When my father made my mother go through really terrible  
situations, I felt furious, impotent, nervous, upset, ........
label: anger

text:
When a person whom I loved and admired a lot died.  I felt empty,  
lonely, helpless, without support, not knowing what to do.
label: sad

text: On my birthday, when I was given my presents.
label: happy

text:
We were riding in a friend's car.  He was driving very fast and  
suddenly a another car crossed the road in front of us.  My  
friend had to turn the car rapidly.
label: fear

text:
When I found one of my new pullovers wrinkled inside the  
wardrobe.  My brother had done it.
label: anger

text:
When I went to see the result of an exam and saw that I had  
failed.
label: sad

text:
The final marks were to be given in the morning.  I wanted to get  
there late because I was very afraid.  When I arrived there,  
everybody was very happy and I had also passed.  We had a  
wonderful time all day long.
label: happy

text:
I went to visit a friend in hospital.  He was going to be  
operated the next day.  I was afraid that they would not let me  
in and I did not know what his reaction would be on seeing me.
label: fear

text:
A friend of mine played a joke on another friend over the  
telephone.  This friend, crying, called me and I got very angry  
and made the other person apologize.
label: anger

text:
A friend of mine told me that my boyfriend had been with another  
girl this Summer.  We had been going out together for four years  
and we had not done so for the last three months.  I could not  
believe it.
label: sad

text: On holiday, seeing the lanscape in Gerona.
label: happy

text: Travelling by coach on a rather narrow and wet road.
label: fear

text:
They wanted me to pay for a ticket twice because they said that  
the one I had was out of date.
label: anger

text: When I came back from my holidays.
label: sad

text:
When some friends of mine asked me to go camping with them for a  
fortnight.
label: happy

text:
Once, when I was very young, my mother left me alone in the  
house and came back very late.
label: fear

text:
When my aunt told me angrily that I was a good-for-nothing and  
she was fed up with my behaviour.
label: anger

text:
When my parents and sister went on a trip and I was separated  
from them for about three months.
label: sad

text:
I phoned a friend of mine to ask her for news about the marks in  
an exam.  She told me that I had passed.
label: happy

text:
I was spending my summer holidays in a village.  My friend and I  
were coming back from a discotheque at night and we heard a noise  
from an alley.  We were very scared and we got into my friend's house.  
 A moment later, an unknown car picked up a person from this  
alley.
label: fear

text:
My mother and I had an argument over buying some clothes for me.   
She did not accept the fact that I did not like the same things  
as her, and we ended up shouting at each other.
label: anger

text:
One day, I was home and there was a phone call informing me that  
some of my relatives had died in an accident.
label: sad

text:
I was told that I had passed the statistics exam.  I had not  
expected this so I was very happy.
label: happy

text:
When my brother hit his head and lost consciousness at the sports  
practice.  For some time he could not remember what had happened  
but he recovered later.
label: fear

text:
I get angry with my brothers and sisters when they do something  
that I do not like.  They know this and still do it so as to  
tease me.
label: anger

text: When my grandfather died.
label: sad

text:
When I spoke to my daughter and wished her luck for the  
examinations she was about to take.
label: happy

text:
When I was told that my daughter, who is at a boarding school,  
was very ill and that they needed me there the same day.
label: fear

text:
One day in a clinic, the father of a child came in and assaulted  
a colleague for something that she had not done deliberately.
label: anger

text: When I was told that my uncle had passed away.
label: sad

text:
When a cousin of mine was discharged from the hospital after        
a long illness.  I had thought that this illness would never end.
label: happy

text:
When a man who had a knife grabbed me and threatened me with it,    
during my holidays in Monze.
label: fear

text:
A certain friend tried to push me off a seat in a very violent  
way for no apparent reason.  It may be that he was excited about  
something.
label: anger

text:
When the neighbour of a friend of mine was stabbed to death by  
thieves in Kabwe.  They stole his van.
label: sad

text:
After going through much shame, I became a Christian and  
something new happened in my heart.  Joy that overflows was  
manifest in me.
label: happy

text:
When I was about six years old, I mistook a cat for a leopard       
when it entered my room at night.
label: fear

text:
When a person the same age as me insisted that I call him  
"Mister".  I refused to succumb, but he persisted and I got angry  
as he had belittled me.
label: anger

text:
When I lost my father on the 25th of September,1970.  He died of  
a sore on the leg.
label: sad

text: When I first passed a job interview.
label: happy

text:
I was almost caught in the girls hostel by the security men, I  
would have been expelled from school had I been caught.
label: fear

text:
When I was accused of having refused to do some hostel work while  
I was at school.  Actually I had not been allocated any work.
label: anger

text:
A friend of mine could not make it back to Unza after having  
failed the exams.
label: sad

text: When I heard that I had made it to the second year at UNZA.
label: happy

text:
When my father's home was to be broken into by thieves who had  
guns.
label: fear

text:
When a friend tried to back bite me on false grounds.  This made  
me wonder if he was a really a good friend.
label: anger

text: When my girlfriend's nephew passed away.
label: sad

text:
When I hooked a girl in Kitwe.  She was very beautiful for my  
standards, a rare bird of this kind accepted me as a boyfriend.
label: happy

text: When someone tried to bewitch me and my friends at night.
label: fear

text:
When I was victimized for running away with a girl who was  
somebody else's wife and niece at the same time.  I was very  
angry over this issue because I was told to pay him money after  
having been punished for it.
label: anger

text:
1976, Soweto uprising in South Africa and the racist Gout's  
reaction to the students demands concerning the educational  
system.
label: sad

text:
When I was accepted for further education, here at the  
university.
label: happy

text:
When I was walking at night, I saw fire suspended in the air and  
it was split into several segments by something I could not see.   
I suspected that it was witch-craft.
label: fear

text:
When I was accused by my brother of having stolen a 5 kwatcha  
note from my mother's bag.  I was beaten up for this, the money  
was found later.
label: anger

text:
When I received a message that my brother was seriously ill and  
was in hospital.
label: sad

text: When I got first division in the exams before leaving school.
label: happy

text:
When I went to town in a double dekker bus.  The bus was about to  
fall on the way when the driver controlled it.  It had almost  
fallen.
label: fear

text:
When I was in form 3, my aunts lied to my daddy telling him that  
I had told them that I was pregnant.  My daddy  told my mother  
and she asked me if it was true.  I was very angry with my aunts.
label: anger

text: When I received a letter telling me that my mother was very ill.
label: sad

text: When I had my four children.
label: happy

text: When two of my children were critically ill with measles.
label: fear

text: When I got a low grade in an administration course.
label: anger

text: When I got divorced from my husband after ten years of marriage.
label: sad

text:
This happened when I went to check my first year results, I had   
thought that I would fail and I found that I had a clear pass in  
all my courses.
label: happy

text:
When I woke up at night to find a fire spreading towards the bed  
-rooms.  I was very frightened as I realized that I faced death.
label: fear

text: When a friend of mine was trying to make a fool out of me.
label: anger

text:
I experienced this emotion when my friend committed suicide after  
we had spent the afternoon playing and discussing life and it's  
problems.
label: sad

text: When I was told that I had passed the exams.
label: happy

text: When a thief broke into my house at night.
label: fear

text: When my sister broke my china tea set.
label: anger

text: I felt very sad when my son died after a short illness.
label: sad

text: When I learnt that I was selected for form I.
label: happy

text: When I was nearly beaten up by the brother of my girlfriend.
label: fear

text:
When I heard that my girlfriend was talking behind my back and  
looking down on me.
label: anger

text:
When a friend, who has been with me at school, failed to make it  
to UNZA.
label: sad

text: When I passed the grade 7 exam.
label: happy

text:
When I was told by the doctor, after many months of coughing,  
that I had tuberculosis.

 In Luapula I was the youngest member of the team and I scored

 seen him a few weeks earlier and it seemed that he had just been

would come to pick me up.  One day he did not come, it started  
getting very dark and I had no money on me and my home was very,  
very far away.
label: fear

text:
One day I had an appointment with my boyfriend which I had  
objected to in the begining, however he visited me and convinced

for over an hour.
label: anger

text:
When my grandmother passed away.  We had been waiting for it as

label: sad

text:

Last night, I dreamt that things that looked like monsters were

For my parents anniversary, we hosted a party and we were very

 nearly overturned on the Lusaka-Kabwe road.

text:
I received a grade above average on a midterm (chemistry) and I

text:
I was walking home from a place on southside and I live on

text:
Someone signed up for a workshift at the co-op where I live and

She had mentioned earlier that she wanted and needed the  
workshift to me so I did not sign up.
label: anger

text:
I did not do as well as I expected on a chemistry exam. I

label: sad

text:
Right before I went to a concert with my last boyfriend he told  
me that although he told me he was going to take me to the  
concert, he didn't want to see me anymore. After that we stayed  
overnight and I said "well, when he leaves me I will be ruined  
for awhile, but for now we're together." I woke up in his arms  
and it was the happiest moment of my life.
label: happy

text:
I was river rafting in Nev. and our boat tipped over and I was  
sucked under in to some rocks and got stuck and all I could think  
was that I was going to die. And it was so quiet under the water  
it seemed like no one would care or remember.
label: fear

text:
One of my first boyfriends got mad at me because a lot of my  
close friends were guys and he didn't want me to see them anymore  
because he was jealous.
label: anger

text:
I was watching a sunset after my latest boyfriend left me and I  
realized that we would never watch sunsets again, probaly never  
see eachother again and none of it mattered.
label: sad

text: I felt extreme joy the day I was baptized. I was one with God.
label: happy

text:
I felt fear when my friend and I broke into an abandoned military  
base in Los Angeles this summer. I feared because I didn't want

label: fear

text:
I experienced anger most recently when I had committed a sin  
which I had gone a week and a half without doing. I had made a

label: anger

text:

text: Finally being asked by someone to a banquet.

text:
A few weeks back, as I was in a hurry to leave the house, I left

we were always doing things like  this.  This really got me mad.
label: anger

text:

 She left and I had to do without supper.

Examinations which we hoped she was going to pass with  
distinctions.
label: anger

text:
I felt sad when I heard that my girlfriend was double-crossing me  
with the boy who is my best friend.
label: sad

text: The joy came when I first proposed a girl at Secondary School.
label: happy

text:
As I was in a ward one man died and I was instructed to watch the  
last offices. But this was my first time to see a dead person -  
fear came.
label: fear

text:
I was very angry when I heard that my brother was beaten by his  
friends.
label: anger

text:
I was very sad when I heard about the death of my teacher who  
taught me in Standard 8.
label: sad

text: My sister gave birth to twins, healthy ones.
label: happy

text:
I was looking after my father's sheen in the forest. One day  
while playing with friends from neighbouring villages the flock  
escaped me and went into a far place. It became dark and I was  
afraid of father. I went home and hid myself.
label: fear

text:
I planned to travel a distance of 20 kilometres on my bike. I  
planned this when I was working in the hospital. When I went to  
the house I found that a friend had taken my bike without my  
consent.
label: anger

text:
It was in the evening when I heard that my girl went to Zambia  
and that she would never come back.
label: sad

text:
This emotion happened when I passed my primary school examination  
and was selected for Secondary School.
label: happy

text:
At primary school I was accused by some boys of being in love  
with a certain girl in their class so they had to shout and beat  
the girl and the matter was reported to the headmaster.
label: fear

text:
I was very angry when one day I went to see my girlfriend I  
talked to her and could not answer back. She was depressed for  
reasons which were not known to me.
label: anger

text:
I was very sad when I was shouted at by Uncle and was told that I  
was not to be given school fees because I didn't go to work in  
the garden since I had gone to escort my sister to the bus depot.
label: sad

text:
It was August 30th when I heard on the radio that I passed my  
M.C.E. exams and I was really happy and joyous because of the  
event.
label: happy

text:
I was walking alone along the place where people fear that there  
are always thieves there and the people who kill their friends  
during the night two months ago.
label: fear

text:
I once was accused of falling in love with someone's girlfriend  
which was not true because the girl was just a friend of mine.
label: anger

text:
It was when I failed standard 8 exams while all my friends  
passed and went to secondary school. In class I was always  
getting more marks than they did.
label: sad

text:
It was when I was allowed to take my wife away from her parents  
after being refused for three times on grounds that she should  
first write her examination.
label: happy

text:
When two hyenas made crying noise on the window of my bedroom at  
home when I was preparing for my MCE examination during the  
night.
label: fear

text:
It was when my Instructor awoke me late at night to get prepared  
for the training at Military college when he was coming back from  
his personal social activities.
label: anger

text:
I slept in a tent at the Barracks which caught fire at night and  
my best possessions got burnt in there.
label: sad

text:
This came in when at one time I met a girl who I didn't expect to  
fall in love with me. Fortunately I tried my luck and she accepted  
my proposal. At the same time she was giving me a lot of money  
which was just like a miracle to me.
label: happy

text: When I was travelling at night.
label: fear

text:
I experienced this when one of my friends reported to the  
Headmaster that I had gone out for beer, whilst the information  
was not true at all. So I had to fight the friend before the  
Headmaster.
label: anger

text: When I was at school.
label: sad

text:
That was soon after the results of the interview which nearly  
9,000 people attended in all the three regions of Malawi. My joy  
came after hearing on the radio that I was one of the people  
selected to undergo the Medical Assistant training at the  
L.S.H.S.
label: happy

text:
Fear came towards the end of May when the P.T.S. results were out  
after hearing the failure of my fellow three friends.
label: fear

text:
I was once this week angry when soemone trying to compress my  
mind due to his nonsense speech which himself could not tolerate  
at all.
label: anger

text:
This condition accumulated in my mind when funeral news was  
brought to my awareness, that a close relative had passed away.
label: sad

text:
It was when I was selected to go to a Secondary school to start  
form I.
label: happy

text:
It was when I stepped on a python (snake) unknowingly while it  
was sleeping near a baobab tree.
label: fear

text:
It was when my friend had stolen my money (K10) and had  
disappeared.
label: anger

text:
It was when my father was taken into detention by the CIDS for  
two years for a reason I don't know up to now.
label: sad

text:
Time had struck 8 o'clock when I heard from the radio that I had  
been selected to Robert Blake Secondary School for Form I. I was  
very happy for the selection. My parents and I were very happy  
and full of joy.
label: happy

text:
My brother had bowel obstruction, having heard that he was going  
for surgery, I was afraid he might not come back to life after  
hearing of the General Anaesthesia.
label: fear

text: I felt very angry after one driver had run over my beloved niece.
label: anger

text:
I was away to school (Primary). In my abscence my young brother  
at home got sick suddenly. My parents took him to hospital. On  
the way he died. It came to me as a sad, sudden and shocking  
news and I felt very sad.
label: sad

text:
When I heard that I had passed Primary School Leaving Certificate  
and was selected to go for Secondary education.
label: happy

text:
When I heard that there is teasing and bulling at Secondary  
School.
label: fear

text:
When I heard that I was not to be provided with another pair of  
medical uniform.
label: anger

text: When I heard that my father had passed away.
label: sad

text:
I met my girlfriend on the way and she joyfully welcomed me on  
the way home.
label: happy

text:
One time I set up my journey at night going to a certain bar. On  
the way I met my friends and they told me that two people had  
died because of heavy fighting. I proceeded on but with fear.
label: fear

text:
An incident occurred to me when I was going home with my  
girlfriend. On the way, a man named Banda grabbed my girlfriend  
in my presence. I was really angry with him and as a result I  
threw stones at him and he ran away.
label: anger

text:
When I found my baby whipped by my Auntie. I was really sad and  
up to this moment my sadness is still on.
label: sad

text:
I felt happy when I saw my brother at the bus depot after 3  
months without seing each other.
label: happy

text:
When we were going to Nkhoma last Saturday the vehicle was moving  
very fast, so I feared we might crash since the road was too  
rough.
label: fear

text:
When they put the blame on me when I scored the third goal at the  
match.
label: anger

text:
I felt very sad when I lost my three Kwacha at civo Stadium when  
Sam Mangwana was playing some Rumba records. That was not what I  
expected, I wanted some Disco records.
label: sad

text:
On December the 28th I was filled with Joy when I was told by my  
bosses that I had been selected to attend a course at the  
Lilongwe School for Health Scienced in Lilongwe.
label: happy

text:
It was last week on Saturday night when I was at Mchesi. I feared  
to cross the Lilongwe River Bridge to come back to School due to  
darkness - until somebody had to escort me.
label: fear

text:
It was at Malawi Army, Dormer Squadron, when some of my workmates  
got promoted to Seargents (sgts); we were having similar  
Ranks.
label: anger

text:
It was mid May 1985, When we had a Test on Nursing. My classmate  
had an answer sheet, so he tried to peep. The Nursing Tutor  
caught him. During this time I was turning my question paper and  
it made noise. This friend blamed me of causing the whole matter  
for him to be caught.
label: sad

text:
I felt joy when I heard over the radio that I had been successful  
in my Primary School Leaving Certificate Examination and was  
selected for Secondary School.
label: happy

text:
One day I was busy day dreaming along the road and suddenly I  
heard the sound of jamming car braked behind me. I woke up from  
my dreams and it was about to crash me.
label: fear

text:
When I was doing my last year at Secondary School I was robbed of  
my clothes, wristwatch and my pair of shoes. After investigations  
it was found that all the things were stolen by one of the boys  
in our hostel.
label: anger

text:
It was on 9th January 1983 when I received a message from home  
telling me that my father passed away on the previous day with a  
history of cancer of the oesophagus. This time I was doing my  
third year of my Secondary School.
label: sad

text: When I had an anticipatory honey-moon with my fiancTe.
label: happy

text:
When it was found that I had gone out of the school premises  
without permisssion and at the wrong time.
label: fear

text:
When a classmate hit me on my occipital region when I was busy  
studying and concentrating on my classnotes.
label: anger

text: When my father died.
label: sad

text:
When I heard my name being announced on the radio that I had been  
successful in an interview for admittance for a medical Assistant  
training course. I was really happy and I enjoyed myself by  
dancing to music from the Radio cassette.
label: happy

text:
One time I was injured when I was playing football at School in  
Blantyre. I was brought to the hospital while my leg was totally  
swollen. The x-rays confirmed there was no fracture but  
collection of blood n the muscles. I feared when they started to  
incise the swollen part with surgical blade.
label: fear

text:
One day I was really angry when all my food was eaten by a dog.  
My anger was against my mother because she was careless. She  
didn't keep the food in a hidden and proper place.
label: anger

text:
One day I came across a certain boy who was intruding my  
friendship as lovers with my girlfriend and I was very sad  
because I didn't expect that girl to disappoint me I regarded her  
as being very faithful.
label: sad

text:
When I was selected to start Form I at Chilumba Secondary School  
out of the 100 pupils I was among the 4 who were successful.  
Family History showed that I had done better than all my brothers  
who had passed after repeating for several times.
label: happy

text:
We went fishing some 5 or 8 kilometers off the shore of Lake  
Malawi. Before we could settle down the lake became very rough to  
the point of threatening our lives.
label: fear

text:
I was angered by a classmate who poured soup on to my clothes. He  
was trying to use a short-cut method in getting his supper.  
Coming behind my back, he wasn't noticed by me and as I was  
retreating from a hungry congested people I knocked his plate  
with my head. He didn't accept being wrong but blamed me for  
pouring his soup.
label: anger

text:
I was sad when my MCE grades were out. I had gone for a football  
match a mile away from home. The mail found me there. I was  
disappointed and didn't play the other half of the match.
label: sad

text:
I passed my MCE Examination. at first I was worried but when I  
heard my name I had joy in my heart and I arranged for a trip to  
attend a wedding ceremony.
label: happy

text:
I was studying in class at night. I was in Form II by then. There  
were rumours about an earthquake. That night dogs were chasing  
one another and passed through the window outside the classroom.  
Those who saw the dogs thought it was a lion and were terrified.  
Trying to run away the desks were dragged and there was a shaking  
movement. I thought it was an earthquake and jumped out of the  
window.
label: fear

text: Someone told a lie that I had stolen his money.
label: anger

text:
My Uncle was beaten by his troublesome son. He fell unconscious  
and gained consciousness after some time. That time I was at  
school; this news reached me through someone.
label: sad

text:
I met a certain lady at Mchesi and I proposed a word of love to  
her and at the same time she accepted my proposal.
label: happy

text:
My father gave me money for school fees and I didn't pay school  
fees instead I spent it on beer and did not tell him about this.
label: fear

text:
There was a cup final match between Limbe Leaf Wanderers and  
Silver Strikers and someone promised to give me some money for  
admission fee to watch this game. Unfortunately he did not give  
me.
label: anger

text:
I had received bad news informing me that grandmother and  
grandfather had passed away. The first one to die was my  
grandmother and after two days grandfather died too.
label: sad

text: Passing a very difficult examination which I didn't expect - MCE.
label: happy

text:
As we were going to Area 10 a dog chased me. I was afraid it  
might bite me.
label: fear

text: Brother took my money to use for his own purposes.
label: anger

text:
After hearing the news about the death of my sister, I felt very  
sad.
label: sad

text: When I was selected to a University College of Nursing.
label: happy

text:
When one of my relatives went out at night leaving me and my  
friend alone, I cheated my parents that she didn't go out, after  
they had heard that she was out, I was afraid that she might have  
beaten me.
label: fear

text:
When someone took my writing materials yet I was to write  
Examinations in a few minutes.
label: anger

text: When I failed my Standard 8 Examination for the first time.
label: sad

text:
I felt joy when I heard my name being called on the radio as one  
of the students who had passed the interview of Nursing and was  
selected to start Nursing.
label: happy

text:
I felt fear when one night my aunt and Uncle left me alone at  
their house to look after the baby when they went to a party.
label: fear

text:
I felt angry at one time when I was chatting with friends and  
suddenly another friend joined us and started opposing any  
comment I added to our chatting.
label: anger

text:
I felt sad when a thief stole all the clothes from my friend's  
cupboard at school (boarding).
label: sad

text: When I passed my MSCE Exams and was selected to go to college.
label: happy

text:
I was with my boyfriend forgetting that I had left the house  
unlocked. Unfortunatly a thief came and stole all the kitchen  
utensils. Thereafter I was afraid of the consequences.
label: fear

text:
My best friend started moving out with my boyfriend. When I heard  
this my heart sank because I didn't expect that my own good  
friend could do such a thing, so I got angry.
label: anger

text:
I was sad when I heard that my cousin died because of being  
bewitched by her husband's second wife.
label: sad

text: When I was selected to come here.
label: happy

text:
Somebody told her friend that she would hit me wherever we would  
meet.
label: fear

text:
This was when my boyfriend told me that I was double-crossing him  
with a certain boy.
label: anger

text: When I heard that my friend had started drinking beer.
label: sad

text:
When the church choir came one Sunday after being away for some  
weeks.
label: happy

text:
When I came home late one day. I was afraid I would be shouted at  
by my parents.
label: fear

text: When a little brother of mine damaged a cassette.
label: anger

text:
I was watching T.V with my parents and some pornographic scenes  
came on, I felt uncomfortable and tried to distract my parents  
attention by talking to them.
label: sad

text: When I had my first boyfriend.
label: happy

text:
I and my cousin went to a filmshow at night. We went without  
making it known to my mother. While we were there at interval, I  
came across my mother just close to where we sat.
label: fear

text:
During the Xmas holiday, I and my best friend at Secondary School  
had planned to meet at a Cultural afternoon at the Mt. Soche  
Hotel after missing each other for such a long time. When I asked  
my mother for permission, she told me not to go for no good  
reason. I felt very angry with her.
label: anger

text:
When I was transferred from Chichiri Secondary School to St.  
Mary's Sec. School. I was happy at Chichiri as a day scholer and  
had made a lot of friends. I was going to a boarding and that  
meant parting with my friends as well as my boyfriend for the  
first time.
label: sad

text:
I was filled with joy when I heard that I had been selected for a  
University course.
label: happy

text:
Sometime back, my boyfriend and I were having a walk nearby my  
parent's house. Suddenly we met my grandfather and I was  
afraid that he would report to my parents.
label: fear

text:
One day I was angry with my friend who went into my drawer and  
took a piece of paper on which I wanted to write a letter and  
used it for her business without my knowledge.
label: anger

text:
It was shocking news to me when I received a telegram from home  
telling me that my grandmother had passed away. I had to go home to attend  
the funeral but unfortunately I found that the burial had already  
taken place.
label: sad

text:
I wrote a difficult Exam at one time while in my Secodary School.  
When the results were announced on the radio, I came second out  
of 80 students hence I felt joy.
label: happy

text:
When the week for Exams came. I got afraid as to how I would  
tackle the questions.
label: fear

text:
Last week a friend of mine called on me and said I was moody and  
difficult to persuade. With this I got angry with her.
label: anger

text: I experienced this emotion when my grandfather passed away.
label: sad

text: When I received a beautiful birthday gift form my parents.
label: happy

text: When I was called for an Interview at Kamuzu College of Nursing.
label: fear

text: When I damaged my wristwatch which I liked very much.
label: anger

text: When my cousin passed away.
label: sad

text:
I had stayed for months without seeing mother because our  
holidays were short and my home is far. Some times, mother came to  
see me at school, I was very joyful, and I didn't want her to go.
label: happy

text:
One day during our clinical practices, we had a very ill patient.  
Unfortunately the patient passed away. I had seen him dying and  
it was the first experience. During the night I became afraid  
fearing the dead body.
label: fear

text:
It was during the beginning of the term. I had K100 and kept it  
in my handbag. I left the handbag in the wardrobe but didn't  
lock it. Next time I found that K30 were stolen.
label: anger

text:
My best friend had failed Exams. She had to leave and so we got  
separated.
label: sad

text:
I had an interview for entry into college. The results were to be  
announced on radio. After a long period of waiting the results  
were released. I had succeded - tension was relieved by joy.
label: happy

text:
When I stepped on a snake at home, it was dark but there was  
moonlight.
label: fear

text:
I went to a fair where a guy who was drunk kept bothering me and  
in the end I got really angry.
label: anger

text:
When I heard that my Uncle had passed away in a road traffic  
accident.
label: sad

text:
I was given a gift by my sister. There were many pleasant things  
in this parcel.
label: happy

text:
I was alone walking in a deserted part of the city and I had some  
fear that some men would attack me and rob me.
label: fear

text:
I wrote an Exam and happened to have not done as well as I  
thought I would. I was angry to myself for not having done so  
well.
label: anger

text: I lost my purse that had money in it. I was sad until I found it.
label: sad

text:
The day I was told that I had passed my Malawi School leaving  
Exams and I was selected to go to college.
label: happy

text:
When I was travelling home by bus and suddenly the bus hit and  
the bus leaned against a wall.
label: fear

text:
I was angry when someone stole a magazine which I had borrowed  
from another friend and locked it in a drawer.
label: anger

text:
When my best friend promised to come at my house and I had to  
prepare so many expensive things for her but only to learn at  
last that she would not turn up.
label: sad

text: When I had passed MCE examinations.
label: happy

text:
I was afraid when my boyfriend came home because my parents  
disapproved him of his coming home. I thought they would chase me  
out of the house.
label: fear

text:
I was angry when my friends said that I should not receive  
Nursing Science books because there was a rumour that I was  
intending to leave the college.
label: anger

text: When my cousin passed away.
label: sad

text:
I was filled with joy when I heard that I had been selected to  
come here at Kamuzu College of Nursing.
label: happy

text:
I was afraid to walk through the forest one day when I dropped  
off the bus around 6.30 pm.
label: fear

text: I was angry when somebody stole my half petticoat.
label: anger

text: I felt sad when my father was sick.
label: sad

text:
The time I learnt that I had passed my Malawi School leaving  
Certificate Examinations.
label: happy

text: Afraid of a dead body.
label: fear

text: A tailor ran away with my skirt.
label: anger

text: Cooks refused to give me food.
label: sad

text: A boy I had been admiring so much asked me to go out with him.
label: happy

text:
I was playing with friends then I decided to splash some sand  
into a car which was moving nearby. The driver got angry and came  
to report to my parents.
label: fear

text:
Sometime back another girl who was in terms with my ex-boyfriend  
came to shout at me at twelve midnight. It was because she  
thought I was still interested in the boy.
label: anger

text:
In May 18th, 1984 my boyfriend went to the U.S.A. In December I  
was told he passed away. He had cancer of the Oesophagus.
label: sad

text: When I passed standard 8 exams I jumped, rolled over the ground.
label: happy

text:
I felt so afraid when dad fell ill, he had never suffered from  
that disease since and I had never seen him as he was.
label: fear

text:
I was furious when the teacher pointed out in class that I  
was the quietest girl in class.
label: anger

text:
It was extremely sad to me when I heard that a patient who I was  
taking care of in hospital had passed away. He had some abdominal  
pains.
label: sad

text: The time I first saw my cousin who is living in Tanzania.
label: happy

text:
I was filled with joy when I heard that I had passed my Secondary  
school leaving certificate exam.
label: happy

text:
I was afraid when my mother left me alone to live in our house  
for one month.
label: fear

text: I was angry when my boyfriend did not turn up as promised.
label: anger

text:
I was very sad when I heard that my uncle had passed away  
untimely at home.
label: sad

text:
When my boyfriend came form Rumphi to Lilongwe for a visit I was  
very happy to see him and couldn't believe it was him with me.
label: happy

text:
When I dream of anything terrifying I used to have fear for the  
rest of the day that the dream might come true e.g., being beaten  
(or eaten ?) by a snake.
label: fear

text:
I had been in love with a certain young man who pretended to love  
me but one day I found out that he had another girlfriend who was  
also a friend of mine.
label: anger

text:
I wrote a letter to my boyfriend but he couldn't answer it in  
time so as a defence mechanism I just found that I felt so sad  
about it and couldn't talk to anyone.
label: sad

text:
When I heard that I had passed my end of first year exams and I  
was ready to enter 2nd year because I felt I had failed as they were  
very hard.
label: happy

text:
I broke a window of a neighbouring house and I feared my mother's  
judgement and action on what I had done.
label: fear

text:
The headmistress at a secondary school accused me of banging the  
classroom door when I didn't in front of the whole class.
label: anger

text:
I received a message that my elder brother was involved in a car  
accident and was admitted in hospital.
label: sad

text: When I was selected to start Form I at Malosa Secondary school.
label: happy

text: When a thief entered the house in which I was sleeping.
label: fear

text: When my dress was stolen.
label: anger

text: When my grandmother died after a long illness.
label: sad

text:
I was very joyful when I heard that I had passed the standard 8  
exams. The day I heard the news was the day I celebrated my  
birthday.
label: happy

text:
I was in the house at night and I heard a hyena crying outside.  
It cried for almost an hour and I feared it might break the  
window and enter inside the house.
label: fear

text:
I was angry at the Cafeteria when the cook scolded and said many  
bad things about me without reason. He thought I was among the  
girls who did him wrong.
label: anger

text: I was very sad when I heard that my Auntie had passed away.
label: sad

text:
When I heard that I had passed my MCE Exam, I spent the whole  
day dancing and eating sugarcanes from our garden.
label: happy

text:
When I heard that my father had found a letter from my boyfriend  
and he was calling me to talk about it.
label: fear

text:
When a certain boy went about saying that I am his girlfriend. I  
wrote him an insulting letter to him and called him names.
label: anger

text:
When I heard that my father had passed away. I could not eat for  
a week and was only crying. I could not find the courage to go to  
bath.
label: sad

text:
It was in 1983 September when MCE results were being announced on  
the radio. When I heard my name that I had done well I just kept  
quiet. I was so happy that I couldn't even talk.
label: happy

text:
I was on my way home when suddenly Gule Wamkulu came from the  
bush and blocked the road. I was in fear and didn't know what to  
do.
label: fear

text:
A certain man went to my parents and told them that I was married  
here, when I am here at school. When I went home for holidays my  
parents asked me about it and I was angry with that man.
label: anger

text:
When I went home on holidays I found that my niece and nephew had  
passed away I was very sad for the children were not even sick  
before death but suddenly died.
label: sad

text:
I was joyful when I received a present (2 books and a pencil)  
from the headmaster in standard 6 because I had passed, I became  
No 1 and he said I was one of the pupils who had good behaviour.
label: happy

text:
I went to the prayer meeting at night and unfortunately the car  
broke down, so my other sister said I had to walk alone from  
Ndirande to Chirimba at around midnight. So we reached home at  
1 am. I was afraid of robbers and dardness.
label: fear

text:
I was angry the other day because the teacher told me to sweep  
some orange peels. It was my friends who were supposed to sweep,  
but the teacher told me to do it.
label: anger

text:
I was very sad when I heard that my brother had failed the  
standard 8 exams for the third time.
label: sad

text:
I was happy to hear that my sister had won a prize at running  
competition.
label: happy

text:
I was afraid when I met my Uncle because this time I was with my  
boyfriend I thought I was not going to be given pocket money.
label: fear

text:
I was angry when I had not been granted a leave out pass during  
the last weekend.
